title: mushroom chicken bake
directions: Place chicken in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Sprinkle with pepper and 1/4 teaspoon paprika. Bake at 350°, covered, 30 minutes.
Turn chicken, add mushrooms, cheese and 1/4 teaspoon paprika.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add milk, cheese, bacon, chives, salt and pepper.
Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 6 servings.

title: semolina gnocchi
directions: Heat milk; add seasoning to taste.
Slowly add farina, Cream of Wheat or semolina, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil and cook until thick.
Then add cheese, butter and beaten eggs.
Then return to heat (slow) for one minute.

title: chocolate dream cookies
directions: Melt 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Dissolve instant coffee in boiling water.
In a bowl combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
In a large bowl combine butter, sugar and coffee. Beat with wooden spoon until creamy.
Add egg and melted morsels; mix well.
Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in remaining chocolate morsels.
Add walnuts and vanilla.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.
Enjoy.
Very rich.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Spray a 2-quart casserole with nonstick coating.
Place cream cheese in casserole; stir in the milk.
Stir in the soup until well blended, then add the thawed vegetables, cooked chicken, uncooked rice, half the Parmesan cheese, pepper and garlic powder. Bake covered in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir.
Sprinkle with the remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered about 20 minutes longer, until heated throughout.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: szechuan cucumber slices
directions: Wash cucumbers, cut in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Cut cucumber halves into 1/2-inch slices.
Place in a medium bowl. Sprinkle with salt and let stand about 4 hours.
Squeeze liquid from cucumbers.
Place cucumbers, garlic and red peppers in a serving dish.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Drain vegetables.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add seasonings, tomato soup and vegetables.
Let simmer 1/2 hour. Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: blueberry dream tarts
directions: Set the cream cheese out of refrigerator for about 4 hours. Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar and cream until smooth. With mixer, mix Dream Whip and milk with vanilla.
Combine powdered sugar mixture with the Dream Whip and whip until thick.
Spread 1/3 of the mixture over the graham cracker topping, then add pie filling, spooned over top of previous topping.
Add the rest of the first mixture and refrigerate.
Chill at least 3 hours or better yet, overnight.
Before serving, to make it pretty, sprinkle crushed graham crackers over the top.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake 30 minutes in 375° oven.

title: italian minestrone
directions: Cook beans with stock and water 1 1/2 hours or until al dente. Add all vegetables, tomatoes, olive oil, garlic and basil. Continue cooking until vegetables are soft.
Add wine.

title: orange silk salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello on fruit.
Combine remaining ingredients and refrigerate.
Keeps well for 3 to 4 days.

title: louisiana crawfish etouffee
directions: In a 2 gallon stock pot, melt butter over medium-high heat. Add onions, celery, bell peppers, tomatoes, garlic and bay leaves and saute until vegetables are wilted, approximately three to five minutes.
Add crawfish tails and tomato sauce and blend well into mixture.
Using a wire whip, blend flour into the vegetable mixture to form a white roux.
Slowly add crawfish stock or water, a little at a time, until all is incorporated.
Bring to a low boil; reduce to simmer and cook 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add sherry, green onions and parsley and cook an additional five minutes.
Season to taste using salt and pepper.
Serve over cooked white rice using a few dashes of Louisiana pepper sauce. Serves 6.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: white marshmallow frosting
directions: Boil sugar and water to 238°; add marshmallows.
(Do not stir while cooking.)
Pour hot syrup over egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients except coconut or pecans.
Beat until peaks form. Sprinkle with the coconut or pecans, if desired.

title: tunnel cake
directions: Cut top off of cake; scoop out bite size pieces from bottom. Create a tunnel.
Mix pudding, milk, Cool Whip and pieces of cake. Put this mixture in tunnel.
Put on top.
Frost with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: caramel squares
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for about 25 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares. Delicious warm or cold.

title: red beans and spaghetti with sausage
directions: Mix all the ingredients in boiler and let simmer about 30 minutes.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix cucumbers and salt.
Add water to cover them.
Leave overnight in refrigerator.
Wash and drain.
Then heat (not boil) the sugar and vinegar.
Cool and pour over cucumbers.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Grease skillet and brown pork chops. Combine other ingredients and mix well. Pour into a buttered casserole. Place pork chops on top. Add fat from skillet. Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until well done.

title: crock-pot swiss steak
directions: Coat pieces of steak in flour.
Brown in a hot skillet for 2 to 3 minutes (salt and pepper to taste).
Add steak, onion, pepper and tomato to crock-pot and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: carrots parmesan
directions: Boil carrots that have been cut crosswise in salted water for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain and put in blender or grate.
Stir in cream, cheese, onion and seasonings.
Pour into a large buttered casserole.
Place pecan halves over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Freezes well.
A wonderful companion with turkey.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: In a very large colander,
mix all vegetables with salt and ice.
Place something heavy on top to weigh down and place colander over a large pot.
Place in refrigerator for 3 hours.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add marshmallows, stirring until melted.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until thick, but not firm.
Add cherries, pecans and cottage cheese; fold in whipped cream.
Pour into an oiled 2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: roasted red and green peppers with garlic and balsamic vinegar
directions: Place peppers on outside grill or under broiler and slowly grill until pepper skin is dark brown.
Turn every few minutes until they are brown all over; remove from heat.
Place in bowl or pan and cover until cool, then peel skin and remove seeds.
Peppers should be shredded in lengthwise strips.
Save all the juices. Mince the garlic and sprinkle over the peppers.
Add rinsed anchovies (optional) to remove excess salt and oil.
Add oil and vinegar.
Serve at room temperature.
May be made ahead.

title: salad bar
directions: Press crescent rolls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes by directions on roll package.
Mix the cream cheese, Ranch dressing mix and milk; spread over crust.
Add toppings, then refrigerate.

title: barbara's potato-cheese soup
directions: Cook together potatoes, onion and 2 cups water.
Cook mixed vegetables as directed on package and add to potato mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer.

title: pepper hash
directions: Pour boiling water on peppers and onions.
Let stand 5 minutes, then drain.
Pour boiling water on and let stand 20 minutes.
Drain.
Add other ingredients and cook 20 minutes.

title: eclaire dessert(lower fat and sugar)
directions: Boil water and butter; take off heat.
Stir in flour and eggs, one at a time, while beating.
Spread in greased cookie sheet; bake 28 minutes at 400°.
If humps get too high, poke with fork.
Cool crust.

title: easy make cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place butter in 9 x 13-inch pan; melt in oven. In a medium size bowl, stir together flour, sugar and milk. Pour mixture on top of melted butter in pan. DO NOT STIR. Drop berries or peaches into batter. Bake in preheated oven for 60 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini bread with apricots
directions: Cream the oil, beaten eggs and sugar.
Add zucchini and mix. Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add nuts, apricots and vanilla; stir.
Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans, which have been greased on the bottoms only. Bake at 325° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: carrot coconut cookies
directions: Mix carrots, sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt in; stir in coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched.
Frost when cool with Orange Butter Frosting which is made by making regular butter frosting with orange juice instead of vanilla.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Marinate pork chops with Mrs. Dash, salt and pepper 30 minutes to 2 hours as time allows.
Sprinkle lightly. Light gas grill; put directly on grill. Turn when reached desired tenderness.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown meats.
Mix together all ingredients, except beans, and simmer a few minutes.
Drain beans and put in crock-pot.
Pour meat mixture over the beans and slow cook about 2 hours.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Place broccoli in ungreased one quart round casserole. Combine soup and milk; stir until blended.
Pour over broccoli and sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick and butter until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lickin' pork chops
directions: Dredge chops in mixture of dry ingredients.
Brown in oil in skillet. Place in crock-pot and add soup.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high setting for 3 1/2 hours.

title: one-hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine buttermilk, sugar, oil and salt.
Sift flour and soda into large bowl.
Mix yeast with milk; add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Roll out and cut.
Melt butter in bottom of baking pan.
Place rolls in pan, turning to butter top.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 24 large rolls.

title: fruit peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix fruit and nuts; add peanut butter.
Blend, then add nuts. Drop by tablespoon.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.
Recipe of Bee Coates.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Guacamole is optional; you may substitute thinly sliced avocados.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine marshmallows, pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Let stand overnight.
Next day whip the whipping cream and combine with dressing.
Mix all together and freeze.

title: fruity dessert
directions: Pour in pan and spread evenly the first 3 ingredients in order. Drizzle butter over mixture and spread coconut and chopped nuts over butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Put in baked pie shell; top with meringue and put in oven long enough to brown the meringue.

title: stuffed frankfurters
directions: Split hot dog down middle, but not all the way through.
Place cheese and mustard into split of hot dog.
Wrap hot dog with bacon. Broil until bacon is done.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Prepare chocolate crumb crust.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 5 minutes or until set.
Cool. Chill.
Garnish.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Let cool.
Chop lettuce and tomato. Mix taco seasoning with meat.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients, except Doritos and Catalina dressing.
Refrigerate.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar; blend in eggs.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Toss together apples, cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar.
Grease and flour a tube pan. Pour 1/2 of batter into pan.
Layer 1/2 of apples on the batter. Pour remaining batter over apple layer.
Top with remaining apples. Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: mocha almond crunch cookies
directions: Tip:
To soften butter, place 1 cube butter in microwave oven. Microwave at High power for 20 to 30 seconds until softened.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Saute onion 3 minutes.
Add vinegar, sugar, cloves and juniper berries and bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Add cabbage.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until cabbage is tender and almost no liquid remains, stirring occasionally, about 40 minutes.
Mix in molasses.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: butter baked rice
directions: Combine salt and 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil and pour over rice.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Rinse rice with cold water and drain well.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until butter is almost absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Pour broth over.
Bake covered in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Add parsley and fluff with a fork.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake uncovered for 10 more minutes.

title: microwave glazed nuts
directions: Place butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High for 1 minute, until melted.
Stir in sugar and cinnamon.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes, mixing well.
Add nuts.
Mix well to coat. Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes.
Spread on wax paper.
Cool slightly.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Simmer squash halves in boiling water for 8 to 12 minutes until tender, but not soft.
Drain and place in a large baking dish.
Fry and crumble the sausage meat with the onion.
Drain and add the remaining ingredients.
Scoop out the squash and add to the sausage mixture.
Return to the skins.
Bake in a 400° oven until warm.

title: shenondoah valley apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla for 3 minutes. Sift 2 cups flour, salt and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients, beating well after each addition.
Stir in apples.
Combine walnuts and 4 teaspoons flour and stir in batter.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan on rack.
Makes 16 servings.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan layer Stove Top stuffing.
Layer chicken, broccoli, then shredded Cheddar cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin streusel squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine flour and sugars.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Reserving 1 cup crumb mixture, press remainder on bottom and halfway up sides of a 12 x 7-inch baking dish.

title: crabmeat mousse
directions: Sprinkle
gelatin over cold water in a medium saucepan; let stand
minute.
Cook
over
low
heat,
stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Add cream cheese, soup and Worcestershire sauce;
cook over
low
heat, stirring until cheese melts and mixture
is smooth.
Remove from heat; stir in mayonnaise and rest
of ingredients.
Pour
into a lightly oiled 5 cup mold. Cover
and chill
until firm.
Serve with crackers.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: mexican candy
directions: Cook brown sugar with milk until it forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and add butter and pecans.
Beat until glazed.
Drop by spoon on greased wax paper.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal and let stand 20 minutes.
Mix as for regular cake.
Add oatmeal before adding flour.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: daikon koko
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and salt together.	It will be very thick. Add coloring.
When lukewarm, pour over daikon.
Leave out
for a few hours, shaking the jar occasionally.	Store in refrigerator.

title: squash salad
directions: Combine squash which has been thinly sliced, onion, celery and pepper; toss lightly.
Combine all other ingredients; stir well. Spoon over vegetables.
Chill 12 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: polish potato dumplings
directions: *Peel potatoes, cook in boiling water until tender, dry over heat and put through a potato ricer.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Brown chops in small amount of hot shortening in skillet; drain off excess fat.
Combine onion, caraway seed, salt, paprika, dill weed, garlic powder and water. Add to skillet.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 45 to 60 minutes or until pork chops are tender.
Transfer chops to warm platter.

title: vanilla fruit cup
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mint leaves.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with mint and serve as appetizer or dessert.

title: malt shoppe pie
directions: Combine softened ice cream and whipped topping.
Crush Whoppers.
Add 1 cup crushed candy to ice cream mixture; reserve remaining 1/2 cup for top.
Spoon ice cream mixture into pie crust. Top with reserved candy and freeze.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: fried chicken tenders
directions: Wash chicken.
Cut in strips across the grain.
Sprinkle with Adolph's tenderizer.
Let set a few minutes.
Add buttermilk.
Mix seasoning with flour.
Stir chicken in buttermilk.
Roll chicken in flour.
Fry in hot grease at medium heat until tender.

title: rivvel soup
directions: Put flour in a bowl; make a well in center and add the egg and salt.
Work into flour with fingers to make small crumbles. Sprinkle into boiling meat broth, stirring as you add Rivvels.
A tablespoon of beef soup base will enhance the flavor.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar together.
Add one egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Add cake flour, baking powder, salt and flavor.
Mix well.
Pour into floured and greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together melted butter, flour and chopped pecans.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until light brown at 350°.

title: confetti casserole
directions: Brown beef, and chopped onions.
Cook until tender.
Add milk, cream cheese, stir until smooth.
Add corn, soup, pimentos and noodles.
Stir well.
Put into casserole dish, sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Can be browned on top.

title: mountain high cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in 3 layers or 9 x 13 sheet pan 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl, except syrup.
Blend at low speed to mix, then beat 5 minutes at medium speed.
Put 2/3 of batter into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Add chocolate syrup to remaining batter and stir well.
Pour over green batter. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lemon cream bars
directions: In bowl, combine cake mix, egg and oil, mixing until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup.
Add 1 teaspoon lemon extract to reserved crumbs. Pat remaining crumbs into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat together the cream cheese, sugar, egg, vanilla and lemon extracts until light and smooth.
Spread over baked layer.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over mixture.
Combine cinnamon and nuts; sprinkle over crumb topping.
Bake 15 minutes more.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: shrimp with spicy sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate, covered, 2 to 3 days. Cook 2 pounds fresh shrimp.
Simmer in boiling water no longer than 5 minutes.
Arrange on large platter around bowl of spicy sauce or arrange shrimp on endive covered Styrofoam cone with toothpicks and top with pretty ribbon.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine beef, onion and chilies in large skillet.
Brown beef until brown and onion is transparent.
Add all other ingredients. Cover and simmer for 35 minutes.

title: aunt willie's salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a large, glass dish.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grandma's syrup cake(50 years or older)
directions: Mix together egg, butter, milk and sorghum.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Stir well and bake in a moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature.
Bring water, 2 teaspoons salt and oil to a boil.
Add acini de pepe. Cook at a rolling boil until pasta is done.
Drain and rinse several times with cold water and cool to room temperature. Combine egg mixture and acini de pepe.
Mix lightly but thoroughly. Refrigerate until chilled or overnight in airtight container.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Salad will keep as long as a week.
You may add more Cool Whip, if desired. This salad may also be frozen, although freezing may alter the texture.
Enjoy!

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugars well.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Add apples and remaining ingredients slowly.
Pour into prepared cake pan (round or oblong).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use vanilla frosting or Cool Whip on top.

title: t j's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, shortening, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla. Beat until creamy, then beat in eggs and continue beating until fluffy.
Gradually add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in both types of chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 100 cookies.

title: peanut butter dream bars
directions: Combine oatmeal, flour, nuts, brown sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add melted butter.
Press 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Mix milk and peanut butter; spread over cooked mixture.
Add M&M's to other half of mixture and put on top.
Bake again for 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Season meat strips with salt; flour and brown in oil.
Add mushrooms, ketchup, butter, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Cook slowly until meat is tender (1 1/2 hours).
Just before serving, add sour cream and stir well.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: guilt-free pasta primavera
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, prepare penne as label directs, using 2 teaspoons of salt in water.
(If penne is not available, use corkscrew or ziti macaroni.)

title: brown bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: cheese spaghetti bake
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, oregano, salt, basil, sugar and parsley.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cooked spaghetti and mix.
Turn half of spaghetti into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Put layer of Velveeta cheese on spaghetti.
Add rest of spaghetti and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lady downtown salad
directions: Heat juice of pineapple.
Add vinegar and salt.
Set aside to cool.
Add jello and
let gel.
Now add remaining ingredients and put in refrigerator.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: terrific corn bread
directions: Mix well together.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 7 1/2 x 12-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: pumpkin or squash pie
directions: Pour the uncooked filling into an uncooked pie crust and bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until done.
A very old recipe, very good!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli according to directions. Drain.
In a small saucepan, saute the onion in margarine.
Add the soup and garlic cheese. Cook until cheese is all melted. Add to cooked broccoli. Pour into a greased baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.
(This casserole freezes well.)

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9X12 pan with Pam cooking spray. Sprinkle bottom with pecans and coconut.

title: yam casserole
directions: Combine everything, except marshmallows.
Blend.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in a microwavable dish.
Heat in microwave 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Mix with mixer until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix with wooden spoon. Pour into greased 8-inch dish to harden.
Cut into squares.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Mix together gelatin, pecans, coconut, condensed milk and vanilla.
Shape mixture into strawberries.
Chill at least 1 hour. Roll chilled berries in crystals and add food color to almonds to tint a delicate green.
Use for leaves and stems of berries. Yields about 48 berries.

title: pineapple cheesecake bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Set aside 1 cup for topping. Press remainder into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Then add Dream Whip already mixed and then mix again.
Put bananas on bottom of pie shell. Add cream mixture and then top with blueberries.

title: southern peanut pie
directions: Spread peanuts in the bottom of the unbaked pie shell.
Mix thoroughly the corn syrup, slightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Pour over the peanuts in the pie shell.
Add a dash of nutmeg, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green beans
directions: Melt butter on low.
Add flour.
Stir until smooth and bubbly. Add salt, pepper and onion.
Take off heat.
Add sour cream. Fold into beans.
Fold in Cheddar cheese.
Melt butter and add to corn flake crumbs.
Spread on top of beans in a casserole dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet pepper casserole
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with crackers.
Next, add a layer of sweet pepper.
Add
a
layer of shredded cheese.
Put bread crumbs on top of
casserole.
Pour	milk over until milk bubbles through bread crumbs.
Dot	with
margarine.
Bake	at 350° until bubbly.

title: andouille mashed potatoes
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, brown the sausage, stirring, about 6 minutes. Drain on paper towels.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoons into hot grease and cook until golden.

title: five cup ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit; mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: white chocolate macadamia biscotti
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, vanilla and liqueur. In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and salt. Add to the creamed mixture, mixing until blended. Fold in nuts and chocolate chips. Divide dough in half. On a greased and floured baking sheet, pat out into two logs (put some flour in a dish to put on your hands, because the dough is sticky). Form about 1/2-inch high, 1 1/2-inches wide and 14-inches long, spacing them at least 2-inches apart. I use parchment paper instead of greasing and flouring a pan, as it is much easier to transfer them onto a cooling rack.

Bake in the middle of a preheated 325° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Transfer from baking sheet to a rack. Let cool for 5 minutes. Place on cutting board. With a serrated knife, slice diagonally on a 45° angle about 1/2-inch thick. Place the slices upright on the baking sheet and return to the oven for about 8 minutes longer to dry slightly. Let cool on a rack. If you like the frosting on them, when they are completely cooled, melt some white chocolate squares or white chocolate chips in a double boiler or in the microwave and spread on the cookies. The chocolate can burn easily in the microwave, so melt it slowly on a low setting, stirring frequently, until completely melted. This makes 3 1/2 to 4 dozen.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In large flat dish, cut up lettuce. Sprinkle garden peas over cut up lettuce, then sprinkle onions, then pepper over peas. Make up Hidden Valley dressing mix according to directions. Pour over salad in bowl. Now sprinkle cheese over dish, then sprinkle bacon bits over top of salad.

title: baby bam
directions: Place all the ingredients in a mixing bowl. Stir well to combine, using a wooden spoon. Store in an airtight container for up to 3 months. Yield: About 3/4 cup.

title: ruby slipper cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs in a large bowl. Blend, then beat on medium speed 2 minutes, until creamy. Spoon 1/3 the batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan. Sprinkle with 1/2

the Jell-O. Repeat layers. Spread remaining batter over gelatin to cover. Bake at 350° in oven for 45 to 50 minutes, until cake springs back when lightly pressed. Cool in pan 5 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool on rack. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: cracker candy
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line cookie sheet with foil. Butter foil.
Layer crackers close together, salty side up. Separately melt butter and sugar. Bring to a bubbly boil, then cook 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers. Bake 5 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips on and spread evenly.
Sprinkle on pecans and press in. Refrigerate 1 hour. Break into pieces. Store in refrigerator.

title: cherry-almond cookies
directions: Advance preparation:
Thoroughly cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk, milk, salt and extract; beat well.
Stir in flour.
Chill.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Shape into round patties and brown each slowly on both sides.
Bake in 325° oven for 12 minutes.

title: jackie's fresh peach pie(jackie clotfelter)
directions: Line pie shell with peach slices.
In a pan, melt butter.
Add eggs and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour over peaches.
Bake for 35 minutes at 400°.
Serve with fresh whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients well.
Stir in drained fruit.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: crisco pastry pie crust
directions: Cut flour, salt and Crisco with pastry blender until uniform. Sprinkle with water, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Toss lightly with fork.
Work into firm ball.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onion and zucchini into butter.
Add mixture of remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients well and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: swiss steak special(microwave)
directions: Set power select at High in an oblong baking dish; combine steak, tomatoes, sauce, soup mix, basil and garlic.
Heat, covered, for 4 to 5 minutes.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pinch off for biscuits. Place in greased pan.
Cook 18 minutes at 450°.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar and water. After yeast mixture is dissolved, mix in butter, sugar, milk and flour. Put out on counter. Make into ball. Butter on top and put into large bowl. Let rise in warm place until double. Punch down. Make into rolls and let rise until double. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook on medium heat, stirring occasionally, until apples are tender and sauce has thickened, about 30 minutes.
Delicious with ham and turkey and dressing.

title: eastern chili
directions: Cook hamburger, garlic and onions; remove fat.
Put cooked hamburger mixture into stock pot and add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and put on lid.
Let stand for 1 to 2 hours, reheating to serve.
For best results, make 1 to 2 days ahead of time.
Keep refrigerated until ready to heat and serve.
Cornbread goes nicely with this chili.

title: halibut scampi
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Saute garlic, green onions and tops, diced tomatoes and jalapeno pepper.
Add halibut; cook until 1/2 of the bottom turns white.
Turn and continue cooking; don't overcook.
Serve halibut in individual dishes with butter sauce poured over.

title: basic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450° to 500°.
Sift 2 cups of flour with the baking powder and salt in a bowl.
Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender or fork or work in with your fingers.
Add the milk to make a soft dough, mixing just until the dough holds together.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, lemon juice, grated onion, Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce and salt; then add mayonnaise. Drain clams, saving the juice.
Add clams and then the juice as needed.

title: christmas punch for 50
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale, and finish filling gallon jar with water. When ready to serve, add 1 quart ginger ale to punch.

title: crock-pot lasagne
directions: Brown meat.
Cook and drain noodles.
Combine all in crock-pot and mix thoroughly.
Cook on high for 2 hours.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Mix sauce, onion, pepper and spices and cook until tender. Mix turkey, rice and half of cheese.
Pour in casserole.
Spread remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave for 10 minutes.

title: danish puff
directions: Mix 1 cup flour and oleo like pie crust with 2 tablespoons water.
Chill.
Roll into two 3 x 12-inch strips.
Boil 1 cup water and 1/2 cup butter to rolling boil.
Remove from heat.
Add almond extract, then 1 cup flour, stirring until well mixed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Put this mixture on top of pastry strips. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting. Sprinkle with ground or chopped nuts.

title: beer balls
directions: Form meat into balls about the size of a walnut.
Brown well and pour off all the grease.
Combine the ketchup, beer, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar and sugar for sauce.
Add balls to sauce and simmer for 2 hours.

title: ludy sprinkle's mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain.
Mix together cornbread mix, corn, eggs and pepper.
Set aside cheese.
Layer in iron skillet:
1/2 meat, 1/2 mix, 1/2 cheese.
Repeat.
Bake according to directions on back of cornbread mix.

title: rosemary chicken strips and fettucine(serves 4)
directions: Boil salted water for pasta.
In a large saucepan, heat olive oil over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and saute quickly to sear. When chicken is lightly browned, reduce heat and add garlic and sun-dried tomatoes.
Saute for a moment until garlic is beginning to color.
Add half and half, bouillon cube and rosemary.
Scrape the bottom of the skillet with a wooden spoon, stirring well. Simmer until sauce has thickened to heavy cream consistency and no more, about 5 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and turn off heat.

title: rose geranium cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs; combine flour and baking powder and add to oil mixture alternately with milk.
When blended, stir in leaves.
Bake at 350° in greased tube pan for 1 hour.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add flour, pecans and brown sugar.
Mix and press in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together.
Add eggs and vanilla to the shortening, white sugar and brown sugar.
Sift dry mixture and mix into the shortening mixture.
When all is mixed, shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.
Chocolate bits can be added to part of batter for variety.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins and drain off water.
Beat egg yolks and cream together.
Mix sugar, flour and spices and add to raisins and eggs.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix all together and cook until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: mustard dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let chill.
This dip is good for raw vegetables (carrots, cauliflower, celery, etc.).
Also good for crackers and chips.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix and chill for 1 hour. Pinch small balls about size of walnut and put into tins rolled in flour and use tart tamper tool or press into tart pan.

title: lattice-top chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, combine soup, 1 1/4 cup milk, seasoned salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: dilly cheese bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Mix all ingredients just until moistened. Pour into pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 5 minutes in pan. Loosen bread from sides of pan. Remove from pan onto a cooling rack and cool completely before slicing.

title: pizza pie cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 6 tablespoons melted oleo and 1 cup oatmeal.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture and to remaining add egg. Press into greased pizza pan and bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and spread pie filling over crust.
Mix reserved cake mix with 1/4 cup oatmeal, sugar, cinnamon, nuts and 2 tablespoons melted oleo.
Sprinkle over pie and bake another 15 to 20 minutes. When cool, drizzle with glaze of powdered sugar, oleo and milk to resemble melted pizza cheese.

title: lucy's pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper chops; bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.
Mix Coke and ketchup.
Take from oven; pour this mixture over the chops. Bake for 1/2 hour at 350° in covered pan or baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over top; bake until melted and bubbling.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Also good with chicken parts.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil; boil 1 minute and remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and pour into buttered dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare vegetables as directed; drain.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish; add water chestnuts.
Melt margarine and cheese together; pour over vegetable mixture.
Put crushed Ritz crackers over the mixture, then drizzle the last stick of margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil for 45 minutes, uncover last 15 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons of margarine until tender.
Combine onion in a bowl with chicken and green chili peppers.
Set aside.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining milk, cake mix and margarine; mix well. Press 1/2 of cake mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces and 1 cup walnuts over crust.
Top with caramel mixture, spreading to edge of pan.
Top with teaspoonfuls of remaining cake mixture.
Press gently into caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining walnuts. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly, then refrigerate.
Cut into bars before serving.

title: rice with spinach(riso con spinaci)
directions: Cook 1 pound thoroughly
washed
and chopped fresh leaf spinach, in 1/4 cup water for
to
minutes.
Drain well. Melt butter in skillet; add
oil and saute onion until tender. Add spinach, salt, pepper
and
tablespoons
capers.
Saute until heated thoroughly, about 4
to 5 minutes.
Add to cooked rice and toss gently.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cathy's fancy baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken breasts in butter or margarine and cheese mixture. Then roll in bread crumbs, patting crumbs on chicken.
Sprinkle pepper lightly on top.
Place in greased shallow baking dish. Drizzle with any extra margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Do not cover or turn while baking.

title: ground beef and sour cream
directions: Cook onion and peppers in fat until tender.
Add beef, browned lightly.
Put noodles in; bring to a boil and let simmer for about 20 minutes over low heat.
Simmer all ingredients together.
Add to noodles and stir in sour cream.

title: crab meat roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, Ranch dressing and crab meat.
Spread some filling on top of tortilla.
Roll up and lay in a pan (any size).
Repeat with each tortilla.
Refrigerate overnight or 3 to 4 hours.
Slice 1 inch thick.
Serve as hors d'oeuvres.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 50 minutes until set.
Top with cheese.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Preheat the waffle baker on medium heat; lightly brush the grid.

title: georgia cake
directions: Mix cake mix, blended oranges, eggs and oil. Bake in 2 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool cake.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with salt, black pepper and garlic salt. Add onion and bell pepper.
Mix with pork and beans and brown sugar in a baking dish.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or microwave for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple kugel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir together noodles, cream, egg yolks, sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir in raisins, pineapple and vanilla.
In a medium bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold egg whites into noodle mixture.
Pour into a greased 7 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until top is light brown.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to present.
Give with reheating instructions.
Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: cajun cornbread skillet casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Add taco mix, taco sauce and water. Mix eggs, cornmeal, salt, buttermilk, vegetable oil and corn. Grease a 10-inch iron skillet.
Pour half of the cornbread mixture in bottom of pan.
Add onion and bell pepper, then add meat mixture.
Pour remaining cornbread mixture on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: banana-sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine pecans, 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; stir well, set aside.
Combine shortening and 1 cup sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla; stir in sour cream.

title: marge's cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Chill in refrigerator for 8 hours or overnight before serving.

title: best ever muffins
directions: Mix; leave batter lumpy.
Bake at 400°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: When potatoes are done, drain and mash.
Add all other ingredients to potatoes and mix well.
Pour in a greased casserole dish.

title: pizza spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and set aside.
Combine eggs with milk; add cheese, browned beef, and spaghetti sauce.
Combine all ingredients before adding spaghetti.

title: mushroom quiche
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add water and blend with fork just until mixture holds together.
Roll pastry out to fit a 9-inch pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: relleno de chorizo
directions: Remove sausage casings.
In skillet, cook sausage until done, stirring to break up.
Drain off fat.
Peel, seed and chop the tomato.
Stir into chorizo along with Parmesan cheese; heat through.
Makes about 2 3/4 cups.

title: coney island hot dogs(milder than most "coneys" with a peppy, tomato-chili flavor.)
directions: Combine chili con carne, tomato paste and mustard in saucepan; heat.
Heat frankfurters in hot water, but do not boil.
Toast split buns.
Place a frankfurter in each bun and spoon heated mixture over.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chicken gumbo my way
directions: Saute chicken, chopped onions, celery, green onion and bouillon cubes in 3 tablespoons butter.
Pour all in large stock pot and add mushrooms, okra, stewed tomatoes and 4 cups chicken stock.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour. Serve with rice.

title: country morning cookies
directions: Stir together the flour and soda; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix thoroughly. Stir in cereal.
Drop by level measuring tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheets.
Place on wire racks.
Yields 5 dozen cookies, 2 inches in diameter.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda in large bowl; add spices.
Combine carrots, oil, pineapple, eggs and water; stir into dry ingredients, mixing well until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing (see index).

title: no sugar jello
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; put 2/3 in bowl and let set until cold.
Mix sour cream, Equal and vanilla.
Put on top of jello; let set.
Pour rest of jello on top.

title: cheese filled pepper rings
directions: Place pepperoni and green onions in food processor or blender. Process until finely chopped.
Remove and set aside.
Place cheeses, margarine and seasonings in food processor or blender. Process until well combined.
Mix in pepperoni mixture.
Fill peppers; wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Slice horizontally and serve.
Makes 3 filled peppers.
Cheese Filled Peppers will keep three days in refrigerator.

title: sour cream potatoes(serves 8)
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until done but still firm.
Remove skins and cut into cubes.
Put into a buttered 2-quart casserole.

title: muscadine pie
directions: Rinse muscadines.
Remove skins from pulp and set aside.
Do not throw away skins.
Place pulp in heavy saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 5 minutes.
Press pulp through sieve to remove seeds.
Combine pulp and juice with skins and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Pour in 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 400° approximately 40 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip to serve.

title: spiced apple pancakes
directions: Beat baking mix, cinnamon, eggs and milk with beater until smooth.
Fold in apple.
Pour batter from 1/4 cup measuring cup onto hot griddle.
Bake until bubbles appear.
Turn and bake other side until golden brown.
Serve with warm Cider Sauce.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in large baking dish, beginning with stewed tomatoes.
Top with remaining Doritos and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: quick louisiana brown rice
directions: In a casserole dish, add butter and rice.
Blend together. Add soup and water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add dry ingredients.
Add milk and cook in double boiler until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked crust.
Beat egg whites and add sugar to make meringue.

title: sweet & sour pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut into chunks, enough to fill 4 quarts. To each jar add 3 or 4 slices of onion, 2 pieces of celery and 2 heads of dill.
Dissolve sugar and salt in vinegar and water; bring to a boil.
Place cucumbers in jars, then cover with hot sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Seal at once.
For best results, do not use for 30 days.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: almond joys
directions: Mix sugar and coconut.
Stir in melted margarine and milk. Spread over cake pan (13 1/2 x 9 3/4-inch).
When chilled, cut into bars. Put 1 almond on each.

title: bohemian nut slices
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes or until yeast is raised.
Sift flour and salt. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in egg yolks and yeast.
Mix until a smooth ball is formed.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually beat in the 1/2 cup sugar until stiff and vanilla.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out each half on a lightly floured board.
Spread with egg white mixture and sprinkle with nuts.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Place on a greased cookie sheet. Make 1/2 inch cut down middle.
bake immediately at 375° for 22 minutes. When warm, sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut.

title: zesty baked eggs
directions: Grease pan with butter.
Break eggs (leave whole); place in pan (use small casserole).
Put grated cheese over eggs.
Mix whipping cream or half and half and seasoning together and pour over cheese. Bake at 425° for approximately 35 minutes.
Bake, uncovered.

title: easy hollandaise sauce
directions: Put egg yolks, salt, mustard, lemon juice and Tabasco sauce into blender bowl; cover and process at mix.
Remove feeder cap and pour melted butter in a steady stream until mixture is completely emulsified.
This may be kept warm by setting mixture in very warm (not hot) water in a separate bowl.

title: soy marinade
directions: Combine ingredients in small jar.
Pour over beef, pork or poultry.
Let stand 6 hours or overnight.

title: creamy cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender in water.
Put cauliflower, celery, onion, lemon juice, margarine, flour, water, bouillon, salt, pepper and nutmeg in blender and blend well.
Cook mixture with 2 cups water.
Heat to just boiling.
Stir in cream last. Heat again but not boiling.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box; cool.
Mix pudding with only 3 cups milk; let sit.
Mix cherry pie filling, pineapple and nuts.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in bowl; add 1/2 of cherry mix, 1/2 of pudding and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook green beans with sliced onion for 20 minutes.
Place beans into casserole, interspersed with cheese. Cook undiluted soup separately and pour over beans.
Top with canned onion rings.
Cover dish with lid or foil and place in preheated oven.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Set aside until partially congealed. Mix together cottage cheese, onion, cucumber and mayonnaise. Fold mixture into gelatin. Refrigerate until firm.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute pepper, onions and celery in butter and oil in a large pot uncovered until tender.
Stir in chicken broth and tomato puree.
Bring to boiling, lower heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash grapes, remove stems and dry on a towel. In one bowl mix 1 package cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar. In another bowl mix 1 package cream cheese, sour cream, and vanilla extract. Mix the two bowls together and add grapes. Spoon mixture into 3 1/2 quart dish. Sprinkle brown sugar over grapes. Sprinkle pecans over brown sugar. Refrigerate. Yield 12-15 servings.

title: once famous pancakes
directions: Soften 3 tablespoons margarine and melt. Beat 2 eggs. Add milk to pancake mix to thicken. Mix with eggs. Add cinnamon and cream of tartar to taste. Add melted margarine; don't overmix. Small lumps make a lighter pancake.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain juice from beets; measure 1 cup juice in pan and heat. (Add water if juice does not measure 1 cup.) Dissolve gelatin in hot beet juice and add remaining ingredients, except celery and beets.
Stir in celery and beets when mixture is slightly thickened.
Chill until firm and unmold.
If made in square pan, cut into squares.

title: starlight mint surprise cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, margarine, eggs, water and vanilla; mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Chill dough at least 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Enclose each wafer completely in about 1 tablespoon of dough.
Place inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Top each with nut half.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 9 minutes until light golden brown.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: big dinner casserole
directions: Arrange cooked noodles in greased 2-quart casserole dish. Cook meat, onions, celery and green pepper in oil until onions are golden.
Season; add soy sauce and tomato soup.
Heat to boiling; pour over noodles.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lucy's cherry nut bundt cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine. Add sugar and eggs; beat. Add flour and vanilla, mixing well. Stir in nuts and cherries. Spoon into greased tube pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar together. Stir into beaten eggs and milk. Add corn and butter.
Pour into greased casserole and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease Bundt pan with 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle pecans or walnuts in bottom of pan with desired amount of raisins and sliced cherries.
Place Rich's frozen rolls in pan on top of nuts and fruits.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding on top.
Melt butter, add brown sugar and cinnamon and stir.
Pour over rolls.
Let rise uncovered overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn out of pan immediately and just pull apart.

title: banana poppy seed chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mash the bananas with a fork in a medium size bowl.
Add poppy seed and milk.

title: baked fruit
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray an 8-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.
Arrange sliced fruit in dish.
Mix marmalade and pineapple juice; drizzle over fruit.
Cove tightly with foil. Bake 20 minutes.
Serve garnished with spoonful of yogurt, if desired.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Slowly start adding 5 1/2 cups of plain flour.
I usually have to add at least 1 more cup of flour, or until you can shape (roll) into balls.
Then roll in cinnamon sugar.

title: chocolate dumplings
directions: Combine margarine, cocoa, 2 cups sugar, water and 1/8 teaspoon salt in a 2-quart saucepan and boil gently on low heat 20 minutes. Make a cake batter of shortening, 1/3 cup sugar, vanilla, egg, flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt, baking powder and milk. Beat well. Spoon batter gently into boiling syrup. Cover and cook over very low heat for 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: Mix flour, oats, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside. Stir together eggs, milk, butter and sugar. Add to flour mix and stir until blended.
Pour batter onto preheated, lightly greased waffle iron.

title: miller's carrot salad
directions: Mix carrots with sugar and salt and let stand 1 hour.
Place in large strainer.
Add celery and raisins; let stand 30 minutes. Stir in mayonnaise.
Let stand in strainer 20 minutes more so mayonnaise can drain.
Serve in scoops on lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: mom's peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in covered glass baking dish in microwave oven. Combine all ingredients except margarine and peaches.
Pour batter into baking dish with melted margarine.
Heat 1 1/2 pints sliced peaches (drained).
Pour over batter and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Blend dates, eggs and juice. Add flour, cinnamon and salt; mix well. Add oil, carrots and nuts. Blend well. Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Serve with non-dairy whipped topping.

title: raspberry jam from green tomatoes
directions: Grind tomatoes after removing the stem and score.
In a 4-quart pan, combine sugar and tomatoes until it boils at high heat.
Continue to boil over medium heat at slow boil 15 minutes. Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Ladle in jars and cover. Store in refrigerator or freeze.
Makes 8 (8 ounce) jars.

title: english cottage pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion and garlic in butter until limp.
Add beef; cook, breaking up the meat with fork, until brown. Stir in carrots, tomato paste and all the herbs.
Add wine or beef broth; season with salt and pepper.
Simmer gently for about 30 minutes.
Spoon mixture into well-buttered deep baking dish. Spread mashed potatoes on top.
Mix cheeses and sprinkle on top of potatoes.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until the cheese is melted and golden.
If you like, you can slip it under the broiler briefly to brown it nicely.
A favorite of my family.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Blend the ingredients well and add clean fresh snow until absorbed.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Heat butter in pan until melted.
Add sugar.
Stir; do not boil.
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs in bowl until frothy.
Add vinegar, vanilla and butter/sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Combine brown sugar, eggs and cream in Crisco until smooth, then add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips as desired.
Spread on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: autumn custard
directions: Combine pumpkin, salt and spices.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into nine 5-ounce custard cups; set in a shallow pan.
Fill pan to 1 inch with hot water.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 40 minutes, or until mixture doesn't adhere to a knife. Serve warm or cold.
Top with whipped dry milk, sweetened with non-calorie sweetener, if desired.
Makes 9 servings, 60 calories each.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour and sugar.
Add onion, then milk and egg. Drop by spoonfuls into deep fryer (375°).
When done they'll float.
Drain on paper towels.

title: southern beans
directions: Fry 8 to 10 slices of bacon. (Let drain and cool, then break into small pieces.) Using part of the bacon drippings, saut the diced onion until tender. Drain string beans. In a good size pan, pour in string beans (drained) and diced tomatoes, then add bacon drippings and onions. Cover and simmer. When ready to serve, use a draining spoon and dip out beans and tomatoes. Place in a long casserole dish. Sprinkle with bacon pieces.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add taco seasoning mix and water; simmer 25 minutes.

title: old-fashioned vegetable soup
directions: Cook tomatoes, water, onion, potatoes, macaroni and meat for 15 minutes.
Add Veg-All and salt. Cover and cook 15 minutes.
You may add more water if thinner soup is desired.
Serve with hot cornbread.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cook and drain noodles; return to pan.
Add pizza sauce, sliced pepperoni, 1/2 of cheese, tomato, green pepper and onion. Place in 7 x 10-inch pan.
Add remaining cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in a 325° oven until slightly brown (approximately 30 minutes).

title: pickled calves hearts
directions: Note:
Calves hearts can be purchased from most butcher shops but will probably have to be ordered in advance.

title: tortellini carbonara
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions; drain and place in a medium bowl.
Cook garlic in hot oil in a small saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, 30 seconds; stir in vinegar.
Add garlic mixture, bacon, and next 4 ingredients to tortellini; toss gently to combine.
Garnish, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: blueberry-orange bread
directions: Melt butter in boiling water in small bowl. Add 1/2 cup orange juice and 3 teaspoons of the orange rind. Beat egg with sugar until light and fluffy. Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with orange liquid; beat until smooth. Add chopped orange and beat again slightly. Fold in blueberries. Bake in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Transfer bread to a platter.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Combine in a bowl and mix well.
Fry in a well oiled hot frying pan.

title: zucchini-potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add other ingredients to potatoes except margarine and bread crumbs.
Grease 9-inch pie shaped baking dish with margarine.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the crumbs over bottom of dish.
Fill with potato mixture and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Dot with remaining margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Saute onion.
Add chicken and cook for 20 minutes or lightly brown.
Add soup, water and rice.
Cool until rice is done.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, milk and cocoa in heavy saucepan.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: chow-chow
directions: Wash tomatoes; peel and cut up in large pot.
Cut up onions and add to tomatoes.
Cut up hot peppers and add to tomatoes and onions.
Add vinegar, cloves, cinnamon, salt, brown sugar and white sugar.
Cook 2 hours or until onions are done.
Put in clean jars and seal.

title: perky cinnamon-apple juice
directions: Pour apple juice and ginger ale into a 30-cup electric percolator.
Place spices and candy in percolator basket.
Perk through complete cycle.
Yields 7 1/2 quarts.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla. Sift in dry ingredients and blend into creamed mixture and shape into balls. Put on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually blend in flour, baking powder and salt which have been sifted together.
Chill dough at least 3 hours or overnight.
Roll dough out on a lightly floured pastry canvas with a stockinette covered rolling pin to 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: First Layer:
Melt butter.
Cool and add nuts and flour. Press into 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: ice cream snickers
directions: Mix all together and spread into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze.
Cut into 8 equal bars and refreeze.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Don't wait until you've earned your first million to try this pie or you'll be missing a wonderful treat!
Mix drained pineapple, cherries, pecans, vanilla and milk.
Add softened margarine, then sugar, then Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into cooked, cooled pie crust.
Place in refrigerator to set overnight.

title: microwave baked apple
directions: Core apples, leaving blossom end intact.
(Using small end of melon ball tool works nicely.)
Peel away skin from top of apple about 1/4 of the way to prevent bursting.
Fill apples with brown sugar, butter and raisins.
Add a dash of cinnamon on top.
Add 2 Tbsp. of water to dish.
Cook covered in microwave dish on High about 5 minutes.
Cook until apples are tender.
Serve plain or with ice cream.

title: deviled ham whip spread(sandwich)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until well blended.
Chill. Use as a spread for sandwiches or stuffed celery.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together; add the rest of the ingredients and blend well.
Put in 2 greased pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy crab-shrimp gourmet(serves 8)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until heated through.

title: heavenly pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and lay across the other combined ingredients in a buttered baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and syrup together until a thread forms. Add hot mixture to beaten egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add nuts and cherries.
Either drop or put in pan.

title: working parents' casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Meanwhile, brown ground beef and saute chopped onion in cooking beef.
Layer, in glass casserole, macaroni (with a little soup mixed in), then peas and ground beef.
Spoon remaining soup over top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add ingredients in above order. Refrigerate.

title: curried beef pita
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook ground beef, onion, garlic and curry powder until meat is browned and onion is tender, about 10 minutes, stirring frequently; discard garlic. Add zucchini, water, salt, sugar and pepper; heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until zucchini is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in tomato; heat through.

title: green chilie pie
directions: Bake pie
shell
for
5 minutes.
Sprinkle Jack cheese, 1/2 cup
of
the sharp cheese, onions and chopped chilies into the shell.
Beat
the
eggs,
half
and
half
and
seasonings together.
Add to the pie.	Sprinkle remaining sharp cheese on the pie.
Bake	at 325° for 40 minutes or until knife inserted in the middle comes out dry.
Put cookie sheet under pie while baking it. Serve hot or cold.
Good served with a salad.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Mix warm water, yeast and sugar.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and blend.
Knead until dough becomes soft and elastic.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Shape into rolls and rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; beat until light, about 2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove from pans.
You can use nuts instead of coconut.
This also freezes well.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift together last 5 ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar. Blend egg and applesauce with creamed mixture.
Combine soda and water and add alternately with flour mixture at low speed.
Blend in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Cook berries, sugar and lemon juice for 5 minutes and cool.

title: chicken tetrazzini(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend liquid Butter Buds, flour and seasonings over low heat in a saucepan.
Stir and cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in broth and skim milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Stir in sherry, spaghetti, chicken and mushrooms.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Add cooked rice, Cheez Whiz, chicken soup and egg.
Bake in greased dish 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken or turkey scaloppine
directions: Mix cheese, flour, and seasonings.
Coat chicken or turkey cutlets in mixture.
Saute cutlets in butter until golden brown. Remove and keep warm.
Saute mushrooms and onions in left over butter (add more butter if necessary).
Add wine and browned cutlets, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Bon Appetit!

title: apple-nut cheese pan biscuits
directions: In small bowl stir together sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl stir together biscuit mix, Cheddar cheese and chopped apple.
Make a well in center of cheese mixture.
Add water all at once, stirring just until moistened. Form the dough into a ball.
Divide into 18 pieces.
Shape each piece into a ball.
Roll balls in melted butter or margarine and then in sugar mixture.
Arrange balls in a greased 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan.
Bake in 400° oven 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in the pan for 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve warm.
Makes 18 biscuits.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Note:
Do
not use electric beater.
Mix by hand.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon into mixing bowl.
Add sugar
and
stir
to
mix.
Add
oil, vanilla and beaten eggs, mixing well.
Add
nuts,
mashed bananas and pineapple, mixing just until well blended.
Place in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for
1 hour and 20 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.
Cake will crack
slightly on top.
May also be baked in 3 nine-inch layer pans
for 25 to 30 minutes or until it tests done. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: last minute noodle dish
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Quick and easy!

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl and beat with electric mixer 1 minute at Hi speed.
Sift flour, salt and soda over this and beat 1/2 minute at medium speed.
Stir in pineapple and blend thoroughly but quickly.
Spread evenly in buttered/floured 9x13-inch pan and bake in pre-heated oven at 350° for 25-30 minutes.

title: sun pickles
directions: Wash cucumber and put in jar. Mix all ingredients and add to jar.
Set in the sun for two days (jar can be 1 gallon or larger).

title: taco salad(quick and easy!)
directions: To make dressing, whisk first 6 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add lettuce, fish and vegetables.
Toss with dressing.
Top with bean sprouts and serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry-chicken spinach salad
directions: Combine all dressing ingredients in a jar and shake well. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Wash, dry and tear spinach into large bowl. Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
May toss dressing into entire salad prior to serving or serve on the side.

title: lemon-coconut cooler
directions: Blend all but lemon slices in blender.
Serve in champagne glasses, garnished with lemon slices.
Serves 6.

title: mom's rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and add 1 tablespoon of butter while cooking.
Let cool.
Pour sour cream over rice and mix well.
Butter a casserole dish, pour in rice mixture and add green chilies and cheddar cheese.
Mix all together and top with 2 tablespoons of butter.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Add to the mixture the condensed milk, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Stir (using hands); will be sticky.
Make into small loaves, then wrap in wax paper. Refrigerate.
Lasts for months in refrigerator.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add cabbage, beans, tomatoes and enough water to cover cabbage.
Cook on medium heat until cabbage is tender.

title: deer fried steak
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thick.
Season with 1/2 of salt and pepper. Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk to eggs. Put steak in dish. Pour egg mixture over steak. Put in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar in bowl until light and fluffy. Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add pecans and chocolate chips; mix well.
Drop by tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until cookies spring back when lightly touched.
Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
May make giant cookies by using ice cream scoop and flattening with floured hand.
Yield:
36 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Spread apple filling in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon and nuts over apple filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over all.
Melt margarine and mix with milk; pour evenly over cake mix.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 8. Good with vanilla ice cream.
Can also be made with cherry pie filling.

title: the best pound cake
directions: With mixer, blend eggs and sugar well; add melted oleo. Continue
to
mix.	Add
flour
and vanilla.
Stir coconut and pecans in last.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Pour in tomatoes; drain kraut and put in.
Simmer until tender, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cream squares
directions: Put one roll of dough in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Spread mixture on top of dough.
Crumble second roll of dough on top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Dough will be soft in the center.
Cool; cut in squares.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Mix the soy sauce, apple juice, cornstarch, minced garlic, ginger and water together for sauce; set aside.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix egg and milk together.
Roll chicken in batter, then into corn flake crumbs.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken in baking pan and sprinkle with seasoned salt.
(May substitute salt, pepper and paprika.)
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm.
Add salt, sugar and cornstarch to milk slowly.
Mix well.
Add chocolate to milk mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount of mixture into slightly beaten egg yolks.
Mix into rest of mixture and cook 2 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into cooked, baked pie shell.
Spread meringue and brown in oven 10 minutes at 350°.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large saucepan, melt chocolate and butter.
Gradually add milk and coconut.
Combine eggs and sugar and stir into the chocolate mixture.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: flavored peas
directions: Cook fresh peas for 40 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Continue cooking until done. Serve over rice.

title: peach glazed ham slice
directions: For glaze, in a blender container, combine peach slices, honey, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Cover and blend until smooth.

title: edna's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and margarine.
Add eggs and pecans.
Fill pie shell with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes more.

title: homemade doughnuts
directions: Heat deep fryer to about 450°.
When hot, drop about 5 biscuits in at a time.
When they get brown, drop into a bowl, then pour some powdered sugar on top of them.
Then it's ready to serve.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix cocoa, vinegar and red coloring and add to sugar and oil mixture.
Beat flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Bake several yams until soft and cool, then pull off skins. Put in a bowl and mash well.
Cut in a bit of margarine.
Add brown sugar, then add biscuit mix until it forms a good ball.
Pat out on floured surface to about 1/2-inch thickness and cut into rounds.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven on a greased cookie sheet until puffed and dry to the touch.
They will be moister inside than conventional biscuits.
Serve with ham or Maryland crab cakes. (From Maryland's Eastern shore.)

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar together, add eggs.
Mixing well, add flavoring.
Add flour, starting with flour and alternate with cream, beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 to 50 minutes. Start in a cold oven.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Mix mustard and yogurt.
In another bowl, mix crumbs, thyme, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. The chicken breasts may be flattened with a meat hammer to make them more tender.

Spread or dip each piece of chicken with mustard mixture, then roll in crumbs. Place in single layer on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for boneless, 45 to 50 minutes for bone-in or 20 minutes for flattened.

title: hot apple slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt and celery seed in 2-quart glass casserole.
Toss with cabbage and apple slices.
Dot with butter.
Cover with glass lid.
Microwave for 4 to 6 minutes on High or until heated through.
Let stand, covered, 3 minutes. Toss and serve.
Yield:
3 to 4 servings.
Nice served with cooked ham slices and Swiss cheese.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Put
all
ingredients
in
a large bowl and stir.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and meat in frying pan.
Salt and pepper it. Drain off grease.
Pour and cover top of meat, slice potatoes thinly and cover top of onions.
Spoon tomato soup right out of can on top of potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or 1 hour or until potatoes are done.

title: debbie's pork chops florentine
directions: (You may substitute turkey tenderloins or chicken breasts for pork chops.)

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain and cool.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: egg salad sandwiches
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and spread on plain or toasted buns.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inches). Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in plate.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour over plate. Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes. Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown first four ingredients in large, heavy Dutch oven. Drain grease and add remaining ingredients, except cabbage. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours, adding cabbage last 1/2 hour of cooking time.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix together except blueberries with mixture for 2 minutes. Flour blueberries and fold in. Dust tube pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: "southern living's" chocolate sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour, baking soda and cocoa; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at lowest speed until just blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: clam dip with zip
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Mix in reserved clam juice, horseradish, lemon juice, hot pepper sauce and salt.
Stir in clams.
Chill to blend flavors.
Stir before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: beef and broccoli wellington
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a medium skillet, brown meat and drain well.
Stir in cheese, onion, sour cream, salt, pepper and broccoli.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles. Press perforation to seal over long side of two rectangles, firmly press to seal.
Spoon meat mixture in center of dough and spread to about 1/2-inch of edge. Cover with rest of dough which has been pressed together and seal all 4 sides well.
Brush with beaten egg and bake for 18 to 22 minutes or until crust is well done.

title: ecstasy pie
directions: Mix flour and margarine thoroughly.
Add pecans and mix. Divide into 2 pie plates and form into crust.
Place in oven and brown, then remove crusts and allow to cool completely.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Divide evenly between the pie plates, spreading evenly along the bottom.
Mix both puddings separately with milk; divide and spread mixture, first vanilla, then chocolate.
Spread evenly.
Cover tops of pies with additional Cool Whip and sprinkle with pecan pieces.
Refrigerate until served.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate the cabbage, pepper and onion.
Bring to boil the sugar, salt, vinegar and oil.
