Pour over cabbage; add celery seed.

title: utah jello salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
While Jell-O is still soupy, add carrots and pineapple; stir.
Refrigerate Jell-O for desired consistency.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cream butter, vegetable shortening and sugar.
Add other ingredients and cook 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.

title: apple cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs with oil until thoroughly blended.
Add sugar, vanilla, baking soda and water.
Beat with spoon until light and fluffy.

title: monterey supper
directions: Cook rice; place on bottom of pan.
Top with cheese, then top with chilies and top with olives.
Spread zucchini and top with tomatoes.
Mix sour cream, onion, garlic and oregano.
Spread mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: medallions of pork
directions: Gently pound pork and cut into 1 ounce pieces.
Saute in butter until brown.
Add enough stock to cover pork.
Add apple filling. Cover and simmer until most of the liquid is gone.
Turn heat up high and add brandy.
Cover until demi-glazed.

title: giant popovers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease pottery cups well with melted butter or margarine.
(I use good size pottery cups.)

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Divide and pour into the 2 prepared pie crusts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl, stirring well. Store mix in an airtight container.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Roll or pat dough into 12-inch circle on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pinch edge of circle, forming 1/2-inch rim.
Mix remaining ingredients; spoon over dough.
Bake until crust is golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: nut bars
directions: Grease pan.
Mix ingredients together.
Pour into pan and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars.

title: brownies
directions: Blend sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend. Add cocoa, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a glass baking dish approximately 9 x 13-inch that has been sprayed with Pam or other oil spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar, milk, egg yolks and salt.
Cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Add vanilla and 3/4 cup coconut; pour into baked pie shell.
Pile on meringue and sprinkle with coconut.
Brown in a 350° oven.

title: ice cream bonbons
directions: Use melon baller to scoop small balls of ice cream.
Arrange balls on chilled wax paper. Freeze at least 2 hours. Combine butter and chocolate. Stir over low heat until melted.
Stir in milk.
Cool. Use fork to dip ice cream ball in chocolate.
Return to freezer until serving time.
Makes 30 to 35 bonbons.

title: taco burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Shape into patties.
Place on cookie sheet.
Broil until done.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie shell by instructions of package. Prepare strawberries; stem, wash and drain. Place in cooked pie shell. Bring all other ingredients to a boil for 2 minutes, stirring continuously, and pour over strawberries. Chill several hours and serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: sweet and sour sausages
directions: Heat all ingredients on low heat until combined.
Add sausages.
Simmer for 45 minutes on low heat.

title: baked beef and noodle casserole
directions: Chop onion and brown with ground beef.
Season to taste.
Add cream of mushroom soup, milk and water.
Cook noodles.
Add all this together.
Pour in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Stir all and chill.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: roll out sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add milk, then dry ingredients.
Mix with spoon.
I always have about 1 more cup of flour to roll out dough.
Make sure dough isn't sticky.
Flour counter top good and rolling pin.
Good luck.
Bake at 350° in a preheated oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies will be white.
I always double recipe.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon crisp and crumble.
Combine with rest of salad ingredients.
Make dressing with mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Toss all and refrigerate for several hours.

title: pork chops and stuffing
directions: In a skillet, brown pork chops in shortening.
Arrange in 12 x 11-inch shallow baking dish.
Lightly toss bread crumbs, onion, butter and one-third cup water and poultry seasoning together. Spoon mixture over chops.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yeast butterhorns
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in small container.
Let it soak while beating egg in cup.
Put the sugar and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Pour scalded milk over it and stir.
Add yeast, being sure to scrape it all out, next add beaten egg and stir again.
Now add 3 cups flour and stir until blended.
Add melted butter (be sure it isn't hot) blend, add 3 more cups flour and stir until blended but do not knead as with most yeast doughs.

title: armadillo and rice
directions: Boil armadillo in salted water until tender.
Remove meat from bones and save the broth.
In a large baking dish or Dutch oven, saute onions in oil until softened.
Add the meat and cook for about 5 minutes.
Add 6 cups broth, bay leaves, garlic, rice, salt and pepper.
Stir and bake at 375° at least 30 minutes or until rice is done.

title: john's chicken soup with rice
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, combine chicken and water.
Bring to a boil and skim off scum that rises to the surface.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add onion, salt, thyme and peppercorns.
Simmer, covered, an additional 35 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken and peppercorn from broth; cool.
Remove chicken from bones; cut into bite size pieces.
Skim fat from broth.

title: nina's fudge
directions: Bring sugar and milk to a boil.
Boil slowly for 5 minutes. Add chocolate morsels and pecans.
Stir just enough to mix well. Drop by teaspoons on wax paper or pour into non-stick dish to cut into squares.

title: cheese and bacon dip
directions: In saucepan melt cheese over low heat.
Add garlic salt and stir constantly.
Crumble bacon slices.
Add along with green onions to cheese mixture.
Serve warm with chips or crackers of your choice.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain juice from apricots and add water to make 1 cup liquid and heat to a boil.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Stir in lemon and orange juice and dash of salt.
Blend in cottage cheese until smooth.
Chill until partially congealed.
Cut drained apricots into slices.
Beat gelatin mixture until fluffy and fold in fruit and mayonnaise.
Pour into 8-inch square dish and chill.

title: easy strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake as directed and let cool.
Mix Cool Whip and strawberries together and frost cake.
Keep refrigerated.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook and stir brown sugar, salt and butter in 12-inch skillet until bubbly and add carrots and nuts.
Cook over low heat.
Cook until glazed, 5 minutes.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and combine with syrup mixture.
Sprinkle 1 cup flour on wax paper; pour cookie mixture on paper and knead.
Roll out and cut cookies with cutter.
Bake at 350° until they rise and fall.

title: frozen buster bar
directions: Crush Oreos and mix in melted margarine.
Blend well (I use food processor) and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save 3/4 cup of crumbs for top.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Spread softened ice cream over crust.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Pour fudge sauce over the top of mixture.
Sprinkle with extra Oreo crumbs and freeze.
A great summer treat.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, rice and onion with salt and pepper. Shape into 6 balls. Arrange meatballs in greased baking dish. Cover with soup. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: glass candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and Karo syrup over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Turn on high and put in candy thermometer. Let boil until 310° is reached.
Do not stir.
Watch closely, as it may boil over.
When temperature is reached, take off heat. Add flavoring and coloring.
Pour into shallow flat pan.
Let cool completely (overnight is best).
Break into bite size pieces. Toss with powdered sugar.

title: busy day cobbler
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add milk.
Melt oleo in bottom of pan or deep dish.
Pour batter in melted oleo (do not stir).
Pour can of fruit (your choice) over batter.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over top of fruit (do not stir).
Bake in a 350° oven until crust rises to top and makes a brown golden color.

title: sweet potato dumpling
directions: Roll out individual biscuits. Place thin slice of sweet potato on biscuit and pinch dough together. Melt 1 stick margarine in 9 x 13 pan. Place dumpling pinched side down in butter. Boil water, sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon until thickened. Pour over dumplings. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or more if needed.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Line pie pan with plain pastry.
Put in pecans in a layer.
Add mixture.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: quick meat dish
directions: Mix, cover and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: baked fish creole
directions: Place fish fillets in greased shallow baking dish (the dish should be small enough so that the sauce completely covers fillets.
In small skillet melt butter and saute until tender, green pepper, onion and garlic.
Add and heat tomatoes.
Pour Creole sauce over top of fillets.
Place thin slices of lemon over top.
Bake uncovered in 425° oven for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: custard
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Slightly beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, milk, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 30 to 40 minutes or until filling is puffed in center and browned.

title: chow mein cookies
directions: Melt chips together.
(This can be done in the microwave.) Pour in cashews and chow mein noodles and stir.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased waxed paper.
Refrigerate.
Store in a cool room or refrigerator.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs, oil and zucchini.
Mix together flour, salt, soda and baking powder and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in two well-greased loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dip meat balls
directions: Shape into balls and brown.
Drop into Sauce mix and simmer for several minutes.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and egg, mixing thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients alternately with zucchini. Fold in nuts and raisins. Chill about 2 hours, if desired. Drop cookies on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Mash and whip potatoes.
Add butter and mix with electric mixer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Place in buttered casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
May be made several days ahead and kept in refrigerator or freezer.

title: hot potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender. Mix with the next 4 ingredients and spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with bacon and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese, sour cream and peach Jell-O together. Stir in peaches.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion and beef in skillet until brown.
Add seasonings. Drain beans and add soup.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart baking dish. Spoon mashed potatoes over mixture and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: unbaked caramel cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add pudding mix and oats.
Mix well.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper lined tray.

title: quick coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package.
When cake is done, use fork and punch holes in top of cake.
Boil 2/3
frozen coconut, sugar and milk for approximately 1 minute.
Pour this mixture over cake. Cover and refrigerate until cool.
Frost with whipped topping and sprinkle with remaining coconut.

title: apple and rhubarb crumble
directions: Combine apples, rhubarb, 1/2 cup Equal and cornstarch in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine water, lemon juice and lemon peel. Pour over fruit mixture. Cover and bake in preheated 400° oven 20 to 25 minutes or until fruit is tender. Combine oats, raisins, nuts, 1/3 cup Equal, butter and cinnamon until well blended. Remove cover from fruit mixture. Sprinkle with oats mixture. Return to oven and bake, uncovered, an additional 8 to 10 minutes or until topping is crisp. Makes 6 servings.

title: taco pie
directions: Mix Bisquick, eggs and milk and set aside.
Fry hamburger (drained).
Add seasoning to hamburger and fry on low until mixed well.
Use pie pan or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Grease pan and hamburger mix.
Pour Bisquick mixture over hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven, add cheese and cut-up tomato.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Take out and serve with sour cream.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Choose firm and ripe tomatoes.
Vary the vegetables according to season (asparagus and garden peas are delightful when available).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut tops off tomatoes and remove pulp carefully with a teaspoon, leaving the flesh around the sides.
Salt the shell lightly and invert to drain. Chop the pulp.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in order given.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread evenly over top of salad.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Garnish with parsley before serving.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in saucepan until hot.
Spray cake pan with Pam.
Ladle a small amount of sauce into cake pan.
Layer sauce, grated cheese and broken up raw corn tortillas.
Top with cheese.
Put in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with sour cream and black olives when you serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: almond torte
directions: Make a	custard
of
milk,
egg yolks, sugar, flour and salt in top
of	a
double
boiler.
When done and while still hot, add gelatin
which has been softened in cold water.
Add almond extract.
Whip
Dream
Whip as directed on package; set aside. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Combine whipped topping, egg whites and custard.
Break the cake into bite-size pieces into deep baking dish.
Pour custard mixture over cake and let stand overnight.	Several
hours	before serving, whip another package of Dream Whip
and	cover
entire
top of cake.
Cover with toasted almonds or coconut.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, sugar and oil until smooth. Stir in the sour cream, making sure not to over mix.
Pour into a greased and floured bundt pan.
Bake in a preheated 325 degree oven for 1 hour.
If top gets too brown cover with aluminum foil. Let cake cool before removing from the pan.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Add onion to broccoli; cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until well blended.
Add milk gradually; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli and remaining ingredients; cook until cheese is melted.
Makes 5 servings.

title: aunt bev's apples
directions: Drain apples; place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Melt butter in a microwave.
Stir in sugar and flour; then add cheese. Microwave until melted and mixture is smooth.
(Stir often).
Pour cheese mixture over apples and bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Place pineapple, sugar, flour mixture and cheese in bowl and mix gently until pineapple is coated.
Place in greased casserole.
Crush crackers and place on top.
Pour margarine over crackers and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Enjoy!

title: pour pizza
directions: Spread pizza sauce over baked layer.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: christmas coconut macaroons
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
On greased cookies sheets, drop by teaspoonfuls 1 inch apart.
Cut maraschino cherries into pieces and drain on paper towels.
Top each cookie with a piece of cherry.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Carefully remove from cookie sheets after 1 minute and cool completely on racks before storing.

title: dutch potato filling
directions: Fry onion, bread cubes and sausage until brown.
Mix together the potatoes and egg.
Add the parsley, salt, celery, pepper, fried bread cubes and sausage.
Mix well.
Cook in pan for 25 minutes with oven set at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Arrange pecans in bottom of pie shell. Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, vanilla and salt. Let stand at least 5 minutes. Add melted butter. Slowly pour mixture over pecans in shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: herbed madeira turkey in roasting bag
directions: You will also need a large roasting bag.

title: nina's strawberry pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and condensed milk.
Add strawberries and mix until well blended.
Pour into pie crusts, dividing equally.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.
Each pie makes 6 good servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Take skin off the chicken.
Boil until done.
Put 1/2 package of Stove Top bread crumbs in bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken over crumbs.
Mix remaining ingredients into a saucepan (including spice package in box) and warm.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle last half of the bread crumbs on top. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: garlic croutons
directions: Cube bread and bake at 200° until brown.
Drench in garlic-flavored olive oil.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, 1/2 cup nuts and margarine until crumbly.
Stir in 1 egg and 1 teaspoon vanilla; mix well.
Press into bottom of a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: cow pies
directions: Cream together the Crisco, sugars, eggs and vanilla, then add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes a large batch.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, carrot, pineapple and vanilla.
Mix until all ingredients are moistened.
Beat with electric mixer 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into greased and lightly floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: easy strawberry jam
directions: Remove stems from berries and crush.
Stir sugar into fruit juice.
Let stand for 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Mix 3/4 cup water and 1 box Sure-Jell fruit pectin in small saucepan.
(It may be lumpy before cooking.)
Bring mixture to boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling and stirring 1 minute. Stir hot Sure-Jell mixture into juice or fruit mixture.
Stir constantly until sugar is dissolved and no longer grainy, about 3 minutes.
Fill all containers quickly to within 1/2-inch of tops. Wipe off top edges of the rest of jam recipe containers; cover with lids.
Let stand at room temperature 24 hours.
Use plastic freezer containers and lids (1 to 2 cup size).
You can store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks, covered, or in freezer up to 1 year.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In skillet, cook ground beef, sausage, salt, black pepper, chili powder and oregano.
When halfway cooked, add chopped tomato, onion, bell pepper and corn until cooked all the way.
Drain grease.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, place meat mixture evenly in bottom of pan.
Spread Mozzarella on top of meat.
In small bowl, make Jiffy corn bread mix according to directions.
Pour corn bread mix evenly on top of meat and cheese mixture.
Bake in oven at 400° until corn bread is golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: pilgrim pumpkin nut roll
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Spread on a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over the dough.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until edges are light brown and have pulled away from edges of pan.
(You don't want the edges to be hard.)

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring often.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix sour cream and sugar.
Set aside for icing.

title: wilma's waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill thoroughly.

title: citrus-avocado salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix with remaining ingredients.
Serve with Orange Dressing on top.

title: moist chocolate cake with fudge frosting
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Add next 3 ingredients and mix together for 2 minutes.
Add last 2 ingredients and mix together for another 2 minutes.
Bake cake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Make a paste of cornstarch and water.
Combine with remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Stir until mixture is thick and transparent.
Serve at room temperature.

title: fancy gorp
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat eggs to soft peak.
Slowly beat in sugar and vanilla. Fold in pecans; coat well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased sheet. Bake 1/2 hour at 250°.
Turn oven off and let stand 1/2 hour. Don't open door!
Store in airtight container.
Makes 55.

title: ham with mustard fruits(good source of protein, thiamin and vitamin a)
directions: Slash diagonally outer edge of fat on ham at 1-inch intervals to prevent curling.
Place ham in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch.
Arrange fruit on ham.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over fruit and ham.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until ham is hot, about 40 minutes.
Makes 8 servings, 450 calories per serving.

title: chardonnay shrimp
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add garlic and cook 1 minute. Stir in wine, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Bring to a boil. Stir about 3 to 4 minutes, while simmering. Serve in wide, shallow bowls with cooking juices. Serve with French bread to soak up juices.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt together in a bowl.
In a saucepan, mix oleo, oil, cocoa and water.
Bring it to a boil. Remove from heat and pour over flour mixture.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk to first mixture. Beat well.
Pour into 12 x 8-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Five minutes before it is done, make the icing.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch square cake pan and line with wax paper.
Then grease paper. Sift together flour, cinnamon, ginger, allspice, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Blend shortening and sugar. Beat well.
Add molasses and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with hot water.
Beat well and pour in prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread half of the cubes on the bottom.
Drizzle melted butter over cubes.
Combine chicken, celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Spread over cubes.
Add rest of cubes.
Beat eggs in milk and a little salt and pepper.
Pour over top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Before baking, mix 2 soups together and spread on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: tuna fish casserole
directions: Mix
together
all ingredients and garnish top with 1/2 cup of crushed chips.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 250° to 350°.

title: nana's shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup, undiluted.
Add cream cheese and heat until cheese is dissolved.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water and add to warm mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into oiled 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill overnight.
Unmold and serve with favorite crackers.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix lemon
juice
with milk, then fold in Cool Whip and cut up fruits.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Sprinkle chopped pecans on top.
Place in refrigerator.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix well.
Put into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: spicy cashew chicken
directions: Thinly slice the chicken.
Heat oil in a wok and add the garlic.
Stir-fry until it is light brown.
Add the chicken and oyster sauce; cook for 4 to 6 minutes.
Reduce the heat to medium. Add green onions, red chili peppers and cashew nuts.
Mix well. Place the lettuce leaves on a platter and top with the chicken mixture.
Garnish with Chinese parsley.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco, add eggs one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Cook 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.
I do not open my oven door for the first hour.
Makes a thick, crunchy outside.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add all ingredients.
Put in oiled casserole.
Top with crushed chips.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain, rinse with cold water and drain again. Chop tomato, onion, cucumber, green pepper and egg.
Add to macaroni.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over salad and mix together.

title: banana mallow pie
directions: Combine wafer crumbs and margarine.
Press into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Prepare pie filling, using 1 1/3 cups milk.
Cover surface with transparent wrap.
Chill. Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.
Slice bananas into crust. Pour filling over bananas.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Cut tops (1/2-inch) and stems from artichokes.
Cut stem close to bottom so choke can sit flat; peel stem and put aside.
Hold choke under running water and as you rinse, open leaves very carefully so as not to break any.
Rinse chokes and stems very well.
Turn upside-down after shaking all excess water off.
Set aside.

title: meatballs with sauce
directions: Combine ground beef, oats, evaporated milk, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Pour sauce over meatballs in deep baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mary sherman's mincemeat
directions: Cook all; save spices until apples are tender.
Add spices and seal in jars.
Makes several quarts and is delicious.

title: bacon water chestnuts
directions: Slice bacon strips in 3rds; wrap around chestnuts and secure with toothpick.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour the catsup and sugar mixture over the top.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°; drain off grease and return back to oven for 15 minutes.

title: turkey-vegetable pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: orange salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in a bowl; pour the dry Jell-O over the top and mix with a spoon.
Add pineapple and oranges, which have been drained good.
Lightly mix the tub of Cool Whip into this mixture and put in refrigerator to set up.
Will be ready to serve in a few hours.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first three ingredients and blend.
Pour over Crispix cereal and mix.
Put confectioners sugar in large paper bag.
Pour cereal mix in paper bag. Shake well to coat mixture. Pour out on cookie sheet and separate.
Let set until cool.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill.
If making ahead of time, add cheeses at serving time.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Saute first four ingredients.
Add to remaining ingredients. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: debbie's casserole
directions: Cook noodles
as
directed on package.
When done, drain and add margarine. In heavy skillet, brown ground meat, onions, salt and pepper
to taste.
Heat mushroom soup slightly.
Grate cheese. Drain green
beans.
Layer
everything
in 12 x 9-inch casserole dish as follows:
green beans, noodles, cheese, meat, mushroom soup. Top
with
a little grated cheese.
Cook for 20 to 25 minutes at
This
recipe can be prepared ahead and refrigerated.
Then cook 10 or 15 minutes longer.

title: egg bake
directions: Brown the sausage.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, break bread until it covers bottom of pan.
Sprinkle sausage over top of bread; sprinkle on cheese.
In a bowl, mix eggs, milk and seasoning.
Pour over bread mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: dee's breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Trim edges off bread and place in baking dish with sides touching until you cover bottom of dish.
Cook sausage and drain.
Crumble and sprinkle sausage over bread.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together and pour over sausage.
Top with shredded cheese.
Cover and refrigerate until next morning and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sowth carolina hoppin' john
directions: Cook rice lak hit seys on the package.
Heat up 2 to 3 cans black-eyed peas in anothah pan.
Cook separately maters, peppah, onion 'n seasonin'.
Serve rice, top wid peas 'n "pot likker", then slop mater mixture on top uf all.
Yawl will hav this'un often - 'n hit don't cost much!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion. Cook macaroni. Drain both and add soup.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted oleo for crust.
Reserve 1/2 c. for top.
Press into 9 x 13 pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cook the following until tender: 1 1/2 c. sugar, rhubarb and water.	When rhubarb mixture is tender, add cornstarch and cook until thick. Cool and spread on graham cracker crust.
Mix the following together and spread over rhubarb: cool whip and miniature marshmallow.
Spread on top: vanilla pudding made with milk. Add reserved cracker crumbs.

title: classic almond creme
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water; let stand for 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
In blender, combine rest of ingredients for 2 minutes.
While processing, gradually add gelatin.
Pour into dessert dishes and chill.
Garnish with strawberries and sliced almonds.

title: john's peanut butter
directions: In food processor (or old-fashioned food grinder on finest blade), grind peanuts until thoroughly pulverized.
(For crunchy type, leave a few peanuts minced.)
In small saucepan, combine oil, salt, sugar and honey.
Heat until warm, not hot.
(Hot will make it harden.)
Put into bowl and add the crushed peanuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Cool.
This makes 2 cups (1 pint).

title: fudgie scotch ring
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch pieces with condensed milk in top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water.
(Water should not touch bottom of top double boiler pan.) Stir occasionally until bits are melted and mixture begins to thicken.
Remove pan from heat and add chopped walnuts and vanilla.
Blend well.
Chill about 1 hour until mixture thickens.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Bring water and salt to boil.
Add potatoes; cover and simmer 20 minutes until fork-tender.
Drain.
Put potatoes in bowl.
Coat with butter.
Sprinkle parsley flakes and serve.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Work in butter and cheese.
Mix quickly and lightly drop by teaspoon on oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix garden peas, green beans, corn, pimientos, onion, bell pepper and celery together.
Drain well.
In a saucepan, bring the following to a boil:
sugar, oil, white vinegar, pepper and salt. Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain
pineapple
and
place in 2 quart casserole.
Mix cheese, sugar, flour and pineapple juice and pour over pineapple. Top
with
crushed Ritz crackers and drizzle with melted oleo. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Boil fryer in about 2 quarts water.
Add salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and celery.
Cook until done.
Cool and debone chicken. Add cream of chicken and let it come to a slow simmer.
Add tortillas.
Cut into 1-inch strips.
Cook covered about 5 minutes or until done.
Add chicken.
If too thick, add some milk or cream.

title: jello-yogurt dessert
directions: Dissolve Jello with boiling water. Add in ice cubes. Stir until ice cubes are just about melted, remove. Pour Jello into Blender. Add yogurt, blend well. Pour into 4-6 glasses (According to family members). Refrigerate until set. Top with Cool Whip and Fruit. Enjoy!

title: no-fail microwave fudge
directions: In a large microwave bowl, combine the first 3 ingredients; stir until well blended.
Drop butter into sugar mixture. Microwave on High 1/2 minute or until butter melts.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
Microwave on High 1 minute longer.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm (about 1 hour).
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 5 dozen squares.

title: chicken veggie pockets
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/2-inch thickness.
Place each on a greased heavy piece of foil.
Layer veggies on top of chicken. Season.
Fold and seal.
Bake at 375° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and cool slightly. Slice while warm. Layer potatoes and chopped vegetables (at least 2 layers) in an 11 x 14 dish. Sprinkle Mrs. Dash on top. Drizzle dressing over all. Cover and let set overnight.

title: quince honey
directions: Boil about 20 minutes (not as thick as jelly).
Put in jars.

title: oreo mud pie
directions: Evenly spread chocolate ice cream into crust.
Scoop coffee ice cream into balls.
Arrange over chocolate layer.
Freeze 4 hours or until firm.

title: baked apple dumplings
directions: Wash, core and peel apples.
Roll out dough squares large enough to cover apple.
Place apple in center of each square. Place a piece of butter, sugar and nutmeg or cinnamon in core. Pull corners of dough up on top. With wet fingers, press dough tightly together to cover apple.
Put a piece of butter and a little sugar on each dumpling.
More sugar and spices can be added, if desired, before dough is closed.
Bake in a 375° oven until dumplings are brown.

title: chicken-dressing casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, and mushrooms.
Stir in chicken. Combine stuffing mix, margarine and broth.
Put half of stuffing mixture in bottom of 1 1/2qt. casserole dish.
Top with chicken mixture.
Add rest of stuffing mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake 25 minutes more.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Stuff chiles with strips of cheese.
In casserole layer the ingredients:

title: fake fried chicken
directions: Wash, skin and cut up chicken.
Pat dry.
Salt and pepper both sides after spraying with the vegetable spray.
Roll in corn flake crumbs.
Place in casserole dish (oblong) or black cast-iron skillet; cook at 350° for
1 hour.

title: three meat baked beans
directions: Brown
sausage	in
skillet.
Remove
and discard drippings. Combine
ground beef and onions in skillet. Cook until meat
is browned,
stirring	to
crumble. Drain. Combine beef mixture, sausage and remaining ingredients.	Pour into lightly greased 2-quart
casserole.
Bake,	uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes a large dish. Good for covered dish meals.

title: silverton drummettes
directions: Boil and bone small chicken. Add salt and pepper. Pop a can of biscuits; roll in flour. Drop biscuits in broth while boiling, being careful not to boil too hard.

title: cuban style black beans
directions: Sort beans; allow them to soak in water overnight or 8 hours. Next morning, rinse beans, then cover beans with water plus about 3 inches.
Add 1 bay leaf, ham bone or ham.
Pressure cook for 5 minutes or in a regular pot about 45 minutes on medium-high heat (watch for water to dry out).
In a skillet, saute until translucent the onions and bell pepper in the olive oil.
After this has cooked, add the salt, pepper, cumin, garlic and oregano. Add to beans and simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over white rice or as a soup.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix in one bowl and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan, greased and floured.

title: tomato bread
directions: Mix and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with a variety of sliced vegetables:
tomatoes, carrots, green peppers, cucumbers, broccoli, cauliflower, etc.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Pour in tomato paste and tomato juice.
Add oregano, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Layer meat mixture, noodles, Swiss cheese and Mozzarella cheese until pan is full.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: crawfish or shrimp casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Cook onions, bell pepper, garlic and celery in oleo until tender. Add soup, parsley, green onions, crawfish or shrimp, chopped pimiento (and juice) and seasonings. Heat thoroughly. Stir in rice and some bread crumbs. Place in 3 quart casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: brown and serve rolls
directions: In mixer bowl combine 2 cups flour and yeast.
In saucepan heat milk, sugar, Crisco and salt until warm to melt Crisco.
Add to dry ingredients in mixer bowl.
Add egg.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough of remaining flour to make soft dough.
Place dough in greased bowl, turn once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise until double, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn onto floured surface, shape into balls or make crescent size or whatever you want.
Place on grease pan, let rise until double, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Do not brown unless you are going to eat them then. Remove from pan, cool.
Wrap in foil or put in bags and freeze. Before serving, thaw 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake at 450° until golden brown, 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk; stir in butter, cornmeal and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cornmeal comes away from sides of pan and thickens.
Set aside to cool until lukewarm.
Add beaten egg yolks; mix thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites; mix gently but thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured 2-quart baking dish and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until top is golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place bacon over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice over bacon.
Place cut up chicken over rice.
Sprinkle with garlic salt, oregano and parsley flakes.
Mix cream of chicken soup with water.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 300°.
Serves 4.

title: crispy cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water about 10 minutes; drain. Combine soup, mayonnaise, milk and salt; heat.
Combine melted margarine with corn flakes.
Pour half of corn flakes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Alternate cabbage and sauce.
Top with remaining flakes and cheese.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°.

title: red potatoes
directions: Boil or cook in microwave, small red potatoes.
Skewer red potatoes, cut in half, and white onion pieces.
Cook on barbecue or Jennaire or Farberware.
Toss in dressing.
Enjoy.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix filling.

title: vera cruz tomatoes
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Drain, reserving 2 tablespoons of drippings. Crumble bacon and set aside. Cook onion in reserved drippings until it is tender. Stir in spinach. Cook, covered, until tender, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream, onion and pepper sauce. Cut tops from tomatoes. Remove centers, leaving skins. Drain. Salt skins. Fill with spinach mixture. Place in baking dish. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Top with shredded cheese and bake 2 to 3 minutes more. Serves 4.

title: mozzarella in carrozza
directions: Cut each bread slice in half.
Cut Mozzarella in 8 slices. Place each between 2 bread slices.
In a shallow plate, beat eggs and salt.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Dip each sandwich into beaten egg to coat.
Fry in hot oil, turning once until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Serve immediately.

title: icing for italian cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, softened with milk if needed to thin out.

title: golden punch
directions: Add water to frozen concentrates as directed on cans.
Combine with the apricot nectar and pineapple juice.
Chill.
Makes 6 quarts or about 50 servings.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Bring butter, sugar and syrup to boil, then simmer 10 minutes, until caramel colored.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Mix nuts with popped corn.
Pour mixture over corn and nuts.
Thinly spread on cookie sheet.
When cool, break and store in airtight container.

title: zero salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well or shake well.
No calories.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and picante sauce.
Brown ground meat; drain, then add taco seasoning mix.
On a serving tray, layer cream cheese mixture, then ground meat, lettuce and tomatoes, then top with cheese.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package; drain and reserve liquor.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until blended and smooth, but not brown.
Add onion; cook until soft, but not brown.
Add vegetable liquid slowly, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until smooth and thick; continue stirring.
Add seasonings and cheese, which has been cut into small pieces.
Stir until melted.
Combine with cooked spinach.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into balls and flatten with fork. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: harvard beets(boiled)
directions: Prepare butter, cornstarch, salt, sugar and vinegar as for a medium white sauce, then add beets and heat thoroughly.

title: broccoli and bows
directions: Steam broccoli.
Cook bow macaroni (don't overcook).
After they're both done, rinse and strain.
Mix salt, pepper and garlic, then add broccoli and macaroni.
Stir all together and then add Italian dressing to your taste.
Serve hot or cold.

title: hot sesame sticks
directions: In the food processor, cream butter.
Add flour, cayenne, salt and oregano.
Mix until butter is completely blended into the flour mixture.
Blend in the egg until mixture looks like cookie dough. Add the Parmesan cheese and blend in well.

title: country baked beans
directions: In 2 ungreased 2-quart baking dishes, combine all of the ingredients. Stir until blended. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until heated through. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend everything in a medium bowl.
Hollow out a sourdough bread bowl.
Break extra bread into small pieces.

title: chicken wrap-ups
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with 2 pieces bacon.
Crisscross slices of bacon and secure with toothpick.
Place in rectangular baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper, lots of soy sauce and lemon juice.
Sprinkle chopped parsley over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cereal nougat bars
directions: Butter baking pan 8 x 8 x 2 or 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Melt butter and marshmallows over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Fold in cereal, nuts and coconut.
Pat mixture evenly in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Pour chocolate on top; spread in thin layer.
Chill about 1 hour or until set.
Cut into bars 2 x 1-inch.
Makes 32 cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Mix stuffing and butter.
Press all but 1 cup into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Next, mix chicken broth and celery soup.
Add cubed chicken.
Pour this mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs on top.
Heat in 350° oven for an hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Season ground beef with salt and pepper.
Shape beef into 1-inch balls.
Heat butter in a skillet and saute meat balls until brown on all sides and cooked.
Drain excess fat and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes, or until vegetables are soft.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Stir in peas, pimento and mushrooms.
Season to taste with salt and pepper; heat until bubbly.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with refrigerator biscuits or cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until done.

title: baked lasagne(river road recipe)
directions: Brown meat slowly; add next 6 ingredients to meat.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick, 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles until tender; drain and rinse in cold water.

title: linguine vongola with clams
directions: Heat butter and oil slowly, saute garlic until tender. Remove from heat, add clam liquid, lemon juice, worcestershire, and wine, parsley and salt and pepper.
Cook on medium heat 5 minutes.
Add clams and cook 3 minutes more.
Add 1/2 cup of hot water and 1 tsp. corn starch.
Cook till nice sauce.
Place over linguine, top with parmesan cheese.
Yield 4-6 servings.

title: company cornbread
directions: Oil a large cast-iron skillet and let it get hot in the oven. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into hot skillet and bake 30 to 35 minutes in 425° oven.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Stir sugar with oil and vinegar. Add to vegetables.
Mix and marinate overnight.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream together the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder (a pinch more to make softer) and soda.
Mix all these ingredients together.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix milk and pudding.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture.
In an 8-inch plastic flowerpot, start with a layer of crushed cookies, then creamed mixture.
Continue to layer.
End with cookie mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight. Garnish with artificial flowers and use a small dirt scoop for serving.

title: vegetable dip
directions: On low heat, stir soup, Jell-O, cream cheese and water until Jell-O is dissolved.
Stir until smooth.
Mix in all other ingredients and stir until smooth.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: whole wheat blueberry muffins
directions: Combine in bowl the eggs, milk, honey, oil and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder.
Make a well in middle of dry ingredients and pour liquid into it.
Mix for only 10 to 15 seconds.
Add 2 to 3 cups blueberries and stir.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 3 to 3 1/2 dozen.

title: dixie biscuits
directions: Stir together potatoes, hot potato water, lard and sugar. Cool.
Add yeast dissolved in water.
Mix together and let set for 2 hours.
Add salt, eggs and flour.
Mix well and knead on floured board.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to use, roll out about 1/2 inch thick.
Place in greased pan, also greasing each biscuit.
Put in warm place and let rise 2 or 3 hours.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: turkey taco salad
directions: Saute turkey in a skillet without oil until meat is brown, about 15 minutes. Add taco seasoning and cook until done.
In
a large bowl add a layer in the following order of lettuce, turkey, tomatoes, olives, then sprinkle cheese on top.
Pour dressing over all. Garnish with chips.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Set aside. Save broth.
Melt 1 stick butter in bottom of 9x13-inch casserole dish.
Add rice, chicken broth, sprinkle soup mix over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: radish and cream cheese spread
directions: Mix cheese, butter, celery salt, paprika and Worcestershire sauce together until smooth.
Stir in radishes and onions.
Chill.

title: kielbasa and cabbage(makes 6 servings)
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker. Cover. Cook on low 7 to 8 hours or until cabbage is tender.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Lightly saute garlic in the olive oil; add this to Italian dressing.
Mix well.
Arrange tomato halves, cut side up, in baking dish.
Salt, pepper and lightly sugar the tomatoes, then add the Italian dressing mixture.
Let sit at room temperature for at least 2 hours.
Top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for only about 5 minutes, then broil to brown bread crumbs and cheese.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Rinse and clean and sort peas.
Soak overnight or bring to a boil and remove from heat and let sit for 1 hour.
Then add bacon and onion and cook until tender.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring to a boil the jello, sugar and water.
Add baby food, pineapple and juice from pineapple.
Set aside to cool.
Mix milk, cream cheese and nuts.
Combine with first mixture.
Pour in large mold or 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: strawberry snowball cake
directions: Clean, cap and slice strawberries.
Mix with gel and set aside. Pinch angel food cake and cover bottom of dish with the pieces. Mix Dream Whip as directed.
Blend in cream cheese until creamy. Pour mixture over angel food cake.
Put another layer of cake over this mixture.
Cover with strawberries and glaze mix.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: souper meat n' potatoes pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of soup, beef, onion, egg and bread crumbs. Press firmly
into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes and spoon off fat.
Frost with potatoes.
Top with remaining soup and cheese. Bake 10 minutes more or until done.

title: fudge
directions: Mix undiluted evaporated milk, sugar and salt over medium heat. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add diced small marshmallows, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute (or until marshmallows melt).
Add nuts, if desired. Pour in 8-inch square buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
Makes 2 pounds.
Easy to double recipe.

title: idaho oven fries
directions: Slice potatoes into 1/8-inch to 1/16-inch thickness and place in ice water.
Drain; pat dry with paper towels.
Pour melted butter or oil on large baking sheet.
Add potato slices to pan, turning to coat with the butter/oil.
Season, if desired.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: swiss cheese chicken(very easy, very good!)
directions: Place chicken in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place cheese on top of chicken.
Mix soup with milk or sherry and pour on top.
Place stuffing mix over all and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, chopped nuts and fruits.
Allow 1 teaspoon mixture for each cookie. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Mix with electric mixer at high speed until smooth and creamy.

title: peanut butter pie(sugar free)
directions: Cook the milk and cornstarch until thick.
Add the vanilla, peanut butter and Equal.
Mix together well and cool, then add 1 1/2 cup Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: reese's cup tarts
directions: Combine butters and sugars thoroughly.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat well.
Combine flour to creamed mixture.
Take rounded teaspoonfuls of dough and place in greased miniature muffin pans. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately put a peanut butter cup into each cookie filled muffin cup.
The cookie will deflate and form a tart shell around the peanut butter cup.
Let cool in pan.
Gently lift each tart out with tip of sharp knife.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and shredded cheese, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add all remaining ingredients except pecans; mix well.
Chill several hours.
Shape into ball; roll in pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: potato delight
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and pour into
a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and soup in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Put onions on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: creamy parmesan cheese sauce
directions: Microwave cream cheese, milk and Parmesan cheese in 1-quart measure.
Microwave at 50% for 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Stir in seasoning; toss with hot cooked pasta.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: crab meat appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese, Worchestershire sauce, mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion and garlic salt by hand and spread on a shollow plater. Pour a bottle of chili sauce on spread. Layer the crab meat on top of the sauce. Sprinkle the top with fresh parsley. Chill and serve with crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: pacific rim chicken pockets
directions: Combine the soy sauce, 2 tablespoons of the vinegar, ginger, garlic and pepper in a medium bowl.
Add the chicken breast halves; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Preheat the broiler.
Combine the hoisin sauce and the remaining 2 tablespoons vinegar in a cup.
Broil chicken 3 inches from heat source for 3 to 4 minutes per side, until it is opaque in the center.
On a cutting board, slice each breast half lengthwise into 1/2-inch thick strips.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until cooked through.
Take chicken out of pan; set aside broth.
Debone chicken and place meat back into broth. Heat broth and chicken to boiling.
While broth is heating, cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in milk.
After broth starts boiling, drop dough by spoonfuls onto chicken.
Cook uncovered 10 minutes.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes longer.
Makes 8 to 10 dumplings.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Mix pudding and place in refrigerator to chill.
Place Twinkies in cake pan (9 x 13 x 2-inches) with lid.
Cut Twinkies into pieces.
Drain pineapple and spread over Twinkies.
Slice bananas and spread over pineapple.
Spread pudding over bananas and top with Cool Whip, about 1/2 to 3/4 inches thick.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix cracker crumbs and butter.
Whip together Dream Whip, milk and vanilla. Add cream cheese mixture to milk mixture.
Take 1/2 of crumbs and line pie pan.
Spread 1/2 cream cheese mixture over crumbs.
Pour cherries over this.
Pour the rest of cream cheese mixture over cherries.
Then top with rest of crumbs.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add potatoes, salt and 1 cup water.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until tender.
Blend flour, paprika and sour cream until smooth.
Stir in potato mixture.
Add milk and heat until boiling.
Stirring, cook one minute and season to taste.
Refrigerate leftovers promptly.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding with milk.
Add condensed milk.
Mix well. Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Layer with sliced bananas and cookies. Top with remaining Cool Whip and pecans, if desired.
Fills a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: burrito bake
directions: Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Mix Bisquick.
Layer remaining ingredients and bean mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°. Serve with sour cream.

title: crumble pie topping(topping for 1 pie)
directions: Cut butter into top ingredients and top pies before baking. Best for fruit pies.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Remove and discard wilted outer leaves from red cabbage. Rinse, cut into quarters (discard core) and coarsely shred.
Put cabbage into saucepan and add boiling salted water and add brown sugar and caraway seed.
Cook 8 to 12 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Remove from heat and drain.
Add to cabbage vinegar and cup butter.
Toss together lightly to mix.
Serve immediately. Serves 6.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Combine mayo, mustard, onions and honey to form a coating mixture for chicken.
Cut chicken breasts into bite-sized pieces and combine with coating mixture in a large bowl.
Place bread crumbs and sesame seed in a large baggie.
Place approximately 5 pieces of chicken at a time into baggie.
Shake to coat evenly. Bake chicken on large cookie sheet (with sides) at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch carefully while baking.
Prepare a dipping sauce for chicken by combining 1 cup mayo and 2 heaping tablespoons honey.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with Cool Whip.
Add pineapple with juice, marshmallows and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit cake
directions: Melt butter, marshmallows and milk in double boiler.
Pour over rest of ingredients; mix well.
Butter pan and pack. Refrigerate overnight.
Take out.	Put in stove about 5 minutes until butter melts on sides of pan.
Turn out on plate.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given, adding dry ingredients and liquid alternately.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes in middle of oven.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Clean and devein shrimp; slit down side of shrimp 3/4 way through, spread out butterfly fashion. Saute onion in small amount butter. Combine bread crumbs, crabmeat, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and sauteed onion. Mix.
Divide stuffing among shrimp; fold.
Place stuffing side down on greased baking dish. Brush with remaining butter. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serves 2 to 3.

title: 5 day coconut cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients all together and put in a tight fitting container. Store in refrigerator overnight.
The next day, bake the cake mix in 2 layers. Cool completely.
Split each layer so you have 4 layers.
After you have stored in refrigerator overnight, stir up the filling and then put cake together.
Put some loose coconut on top. Wrap in Saran Wrap for 5 days or less.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Bake potatoes.
While warm, shred potatoes into buttered casserole dish (2-quart).
Stir in all other ingredients, saving 1/2 cup cheese and paprika for top.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ethel's favorite custard
directions: Mix Eggs and Sugar.
Slowly add Hot Milk; beating with a wooden fork.
Add Vanilla and Nutmeg.
Put 1 teaspoon of Grapenuts Cereal in 6 custard cups.
Then set in a pan of hot water, about an inch deep.
Pour in milk mixture.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Test by inserting a knife into custard.
Done when knife comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold.

title: no seal pickles
directions: First Day:
To one gallon cucumbers and salt and boiling water.
Let stand one day.

title: curry sauce
directions: Melt
butter
until soft; add curry powder and paprika. Remove from
heat
and blend well.
Stir in mayonnaise and mix well. Serve over asparagus.

title: garlic gourmet chicken breasts
directions: Rinse chicken, pat day.
In non-metal container, combine sour cream, lemon juice, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic.
Add chicken to sour cream mixture; coat each piece well.
Cover refrigerate overnight or up to 24 hours.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In small mixing bowl whip whites with cream of tartar until they hold a soft peak.
Gradually whip in sugar.
Continue to whip just until whites hold a firm peak.
Pile onto pie filling and seal to inside of edge of pie shell.
Bake in 325° oven until top is golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Let cool before slicing.

title: stuffed pita pockets
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a frying pan.
Saute the onion for 5 minutes.
Add meat, salt, pepper, parsley and tomatoes.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir until meat browns.
Cut each pita loaf in half and stuff pocket with lettuce and meat mixture.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in flour, chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into a 9x13 inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Do not over bake.

title: cherry berries on a cloud
directions: Beat egg whites, sugar and cream of tartar well and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Turn oven off and leave cake in oven for 12 hours.
Then mix whipping cream, marshmallows and cream cheese.
Spread on cake and chill for 12 hours.
Then mix cherry pie filling and strawberries and spoon over cake.

title: nacho cheese and meat dip
directions: Combine ingredients and cook on low in crock-pot, until melted, stirring often, about 2 hours.
Serve dip hot with tortilla chips.

title: turkey tomato melts(serves 4)
directions: Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
When butter just begins to turn brown, add turkey.
Cook 3 minutes; turn.
Top the turkey breast slices with tomato, green pepper and cheese.
Cover and cook 2 minutes more.
Toast the French bread slices.
Serve turkey breast slices open-faced on French toast.

title: peanut butter novaks
directions: You will need wax paper.

title: tiropettakia (cheese filled triangles)
directions: Blend crumbled Feta and Ricotta cheese and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well.
Add Romano cheese, basil and mint leaves and mix well.
Cut filo sheets into 1-inch strips wide.
Brush each sheet with melted butter and place 1 teaspoon of the filling on one end of the pastry strip and fold corner over to make a triangle.
Continue folding from side to side in the form of a triangle until strip is folded.
Place cheese triangles on a buttered baking sheet.
Brush tops with melted butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 eggs, margarine and nuts.
Spread in well-greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: punch
directions: In punch bowl or large container, pour Juicy Juice over ice. Add Sprite.
For garnish, add scoops of sherbet.
This punch is cool and not too sweet.

title: nancy's punch
directions: Boil water.
Stir in jello and sugar and dissolve.
Add pineapple juice, almond extract, limeade and 4 cups water. Freeze.
When ready to use, add 2 bottles ginger ale.

title: vegetable pot stickers
directions: Heat 3/4 cup of chicken broth to boiling in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium high heat.
Stir in onion, celery, cabbage, mushroom, ginger root and garlic.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes, stirring frequently and adding more broth if vegetables begin to stick, until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soy sauce and sesame oil.
Remove vegetable mixture from skillet.
Wipe out skillet.
Brush edges of 1 wonton skin with water.
Place 1 heaping teaspoon vegetable mixture on center of skin.
Fold skin in half over filling and pinch edges to seal.
Make creases in sealed edges to form pleats on one side of each pot sticker.
Repeat with remaining wonton skins and vegetable mixture.
Spray skillet with cooking spray; heat skillet over medium heat.
Cook pot stickers in skillet, pleated sides up, about 1 minute or until bottoms are light brown.
Add remaining 3/4 cup of broth.
Cover and cook 5 to 8 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed.

title: easy mixed vegetable supper
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish. Sprinkle another 1/2 c. of dried onion rings on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco bake
directions: Layer all ingredients in casserole dish and bake in a 350° preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meatball soup
directions: Season beef with salt and pepper; shape into 18 small meatballs.
In pan, brown meatballs (use shortening if necessary) and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Push meatballs to one side. Stir in soup and water.
Heat and stir now and then.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown turkey.
Add onion and green peppers.
Add V-8 juice, oregano and basil.
Cook a little at a time.
Put one-half of turkey mixture in glass baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Add remaining turkey mixture and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut like pizza.

title: autumn chowder
directions: Saute bacon and onion until cooked.
Add water, potatoes and bouillon.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and heat. Serves 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Add mayonnaise and toss. Put in flat baking dish (7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch).
Sprinkle with cheese; top with crushed potato chips.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent dough on cookie sheet, smoothing perforations. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
When cooled, spread mixture of cream cheese, onion, dill seed, garlic powder and mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle with vegetable pieces.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans; stir just until all ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool in pans 5 minutes, remove to wire rack to cool.

title: cheese roll
directions: Sprinkle on last 4 ingredients.
Roll up and refrigerate until served.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Layer half of the mushrooms, cheese and olives in a 2-quart casserole. Repeat layering.
Mix flour, seasoned salt, Accent and pepper. Stir in half and half and onion.
Spoon over casserole. Melt butter and blend in bread crumbs. Sprinkle over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: applesauce raspberry mold
directions: Prepare jello and add fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: herbed rice pilaf
directions: In a skillet, saute rice, celery and onion in butter until the rice is lightly browned and the vegetables are tender.
Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine all remaining ingredients; pour over rice mixture.

title: grandma's kringlas
directions: Add vinegar to whipping cream.
Stir all ingredients together. Do not use a mixer.
Refrigerate a few hours or overnight. Roll out, like a pencil, about a tablespoon at a time on a lightly floured board and shape to a figure eight.
Bake about 10 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet at 375°.
This is Matt's favorite treat at Grandma's.
Freeze well; serve with butter.

title: low-fat chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, applesauce and sour cream.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until center tests done.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Melt chocolate in milk; stir to blend.
Combine eggs, sugar, salt and add to chocolate mixture; stir until blended; then add vanilla.
Place bread in 1-quart baking dish which has been greased.
Pour mixture over bread and let stand for 10 minutes. Place dish in pan of hot water.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serve warm.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan according to cake instructions.
Pour Kahlua over warm cake.
Cover and let stand overnight.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Press biscuits into 9-inch pie pan.
Pour and press Rice Krispies into biscuits.
Lightly press the Cheddar cheese onto Rice Krispies. Dot with oleo.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain and mix with chicken soup.
Add the drained chunks of chicken.
Pour over biscuit mixture in pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edge of biscuit is golden brown.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, lemon juice and walnuts in medium bowl.
In a small bowl, blend mayonnaise, sour cream and honey. Add dressing to apple mixture.
Chill. Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecue sausage
directions: Cut sausage into one-inch pieces.
Cover in cooking sauce and ketchup.
Simmer in slow cooker for 2 hours or until sausage is tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg.
Beat in bananas and cream well.
Add buttermilk, flour, soda, vanilla, lemon extract and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes in a loaf pan at 325°.
Check for doneness with a cake tester.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pirok(salmon pie)
directions: Roll out half the pastry 1/8-inch thick to line an 8-inch square pan.
Mix rice with 1/2 cup cream sauce.
Place half of rice mixture in pastry.
Add pieces of salmon.
Distribute onions and eggs over salmon, then cover with remaining rice.
Roll out second half of dough and place over rice.
Moisten edges in top crust for escape of steam.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: chili with lentils
directions: Rinse dry lentils.
Pick out any stems or stones.
Add salt and dry lentils to boiling water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Do not drain.
Add tomatoes or tomato sauce, chili powder, onion, celery and garlic; cover and simmer 30 minutes more.
Serve over rice, spaghetti or corn chips.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Cook oats in 3 1/2 cups unsalted water.
Cool slightly, then add salt, sugar and 2 cups cold water.
When slightly more than lukewarm, add yeast which has been dissolved in 1/2 cup cool water.
Add flour to make a medium stiff dough.
Let rise 1 hour; knead.
Make into 3 loaves.
Let rise another hour, then bake at 400° for first few minutes, then lower temperature to 350° and bake 30 to 45 minutes until lightly browned.

title: mustard pickles(semi-sour)
directions: Pack washed cucumbers in jars or crock.
(Should be small or sliced lengthwise.)
Stir mixture of vinegar, water, salt, mustard and sugar until dissolved.
Pour this mixture over cucumbers.
Put covers on jars.

title: frypan cookies
directions: Melt the butter, sugar, eggs and dates in frypan. Cook until it leaves sides. Stir while cooking.
Remove and cool a few minutes.
Place the Rice Krispies and nuts in a large bowl. Add mixture and roll into balls, then roll in coconut.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix Stove Top according to package directions.
Drain broccoli.
Mix broccoli, mayonnaise, can of soup (undiluted), egg and onion together. Spread in oblong baking dish. Top with Stove Top then cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat in milk and vanilla.
Pour into 6 custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in pan of hot water at 325° until mixture doesn't stick to knife.

title: 6 week amish muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, baking soda, salt and allspice. Add Raisin Bran and sugar; stir well.
Mix eggs, oil, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into other mixture; stir.
Fill muffin papers 1/2 full.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Pour rest of batter in plastic container to use later.
Date it.
Don't restir batter as you use it for muffins.
Lasts 6 weeks.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add sour cream and lemon and blend well.
Drain green chiles; stir in with green onions.
Spread 1/8 of mixture on one flour tortilla to within 1/2-inch of edges. Roll up all 8 tortillas.
Chill several hours, covered tightly. Remove and slice in 3/4-inch pieces.
Secure with toothpick; serve with Pace picante for dipping.

title: potato puffs
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add potatoes.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into potato mixture.
In a large saucepan or kettle, heat about 1-inch of oil to 375°.
Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonful, four or five at a time into hot oil.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, turning once or until golden brown.
Watch closely since they brown quickly.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool. Pierce with fork and drizzle coffee brandy over cake.
Cool overnight in refrigerator.
Cut 1/2 cake into cubes and place in bottom of large glass bowl.
Mix mousse as directed and pour half over cake cubes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of candy bars.
Layer with 1 container of Cool Whip, then repeat, saving some candy for garnish. Make in punch bowl or large glass bowl.
Serves approximately 20.

title: balsamic b~b~q chicken
directions: In large resealable plastic food storage bag, combine dressing, ketchup, oregano and pepper; add chicken.
Turn bag to coat chicken with marinade; seal bag and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 425°.
Transfer chicken to roasting pan. Skin side up.
Discard marinade.
Roast until meat is not longer pink near bone, 40 minutes, covering loosely with foil if skin is browning to quickly.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: italian potatoes in foil
directions: Slice potatoes into strips on foil.
Season to taste with garlic powder, salt, pepper, paprika, parsley flakes and oregano. Top each with 3 pats of butter and sprinkle heavily with Parmesan cheese.
Wrap tightly in individual foil pockets.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy corned beef supper
directions: Heat skillet; add oil.
(I use my wok which works great!) Saute onion and bell pepper in oil until translucent.
Add corned beef; let simmer about 10 minutes.
Add jar of picante sauce; simmer another 10 minutes.
Serve over white rice or pasta.
Easy and good!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy apple butter
directions: Mix and bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir every 30 minutes until done.
Put in jars while hot.
Keep refrigerated. Will keep a long time.

title: oven steak fries
directions: Scrub and quarter potatoes.
In shallow bowl, combine water and Tabasco sauce.
On plate, combine bread crumbs and cheese.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Dip potatoes in water mixture and roll in crumb mixture.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, turning once, until done.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crust:
Mix pretzels, oleo and 2 tablespoons sugar; place in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes at 400°.

title: egg nog
directions: Put ice cream in punch bowl to melt.
Add egg yolks and the next 4 ingredients to melted ice cream.
Beat egg whites to peaks. Fold into ice cream mixture.

title: quick butter coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick spray; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, 1/3 cup sugar and the baking powder; set aside.
Using a wire whisk, in a small bowl, beat together the milk, 1/3 cup melted butter, egg and vanilla.
Pour into flour mixture.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan and brush with remaining butter.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add other ingredients, except last four, and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine the last four ingredients together and sprinkle on the top of the sweet potato mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables as directed on package; drain.
Mix in other ingredients.
Top with crackers mixed with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot pizza dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a 1-quart bowl, combine cream cheese and Italian seasoning. Spread onto bottom of an 8-inch pan. In small bowl, combine cheeses. Sprinkle half of cheese mixture over cream cheese mixture. Spread pizza sauce over cheese layer. Sprinkle remaining half of cheese. Top with peppers and onions. Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with French bread or fresh vegetables.

title: caramel microwave popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in a large paper bag.
Put brown sugar, margarine, salt and Karo syrup in a glass bowl and cook on High in microwave until it starts to boil.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Remove from microwave; stir and immediately add baking soda.
Stir until mixture becomes frothy.
Pour mixture onto popcorn in the paper bag.
Roll the top of the bag shut and shake hard.
Microwave for 1/2 minute, then flip bag over and cook another 1/2 minute. Remove bag and shake hard again.
Microwave 1/2 minute; turn bag again and cook another 1/2 minute.
Lay popcorn out to dry on a cookie sheet.

title: prego hearty lasagne
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella and eggs.
Brown beef, stirring to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Stir in Prego sauce.
In each of two 2-quart shallow baking dishes, layer 1 cup Prego mixture, 2 noodles and 1 cup cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles, remaining Prego mixture and Parmesan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: do ahead quick spread
directions: Sprinkle light layer of dried onion flakes over the surface of cream cheese.
Layer other spices on.
Cover, refrigerate and let set 24 to 72 hours.
Remove from refrigerator 1/2 to 1 hour before serving.

title: orange souffle
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar with 1 tablespoon butter and 2 tablespoons flour.
Add juice and rind of one orange.
Add 1 cup milk and 2 beaten egg yolks.
Fold in beaten egg whites and bake slowly for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Set small custard dishes in large pan of hot water to cool.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Use a large casserole dish, Corning Ware is great if you have one.
Melt 1 stick margarine in large skillet.
Mix with cracker crumbs.
Set aside.
Melt 1 stick margarine in skillet.
Add 6 tablespoons flour.
Gradually add 3 cups milk to make a thick white sauce.
Add 1 1/2 jars Old English cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add mushrooms.

title: quick dip for chips
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: world's best bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix and measure out 2-cup portions and store each portion in airtight containers. Makes 20 portions.

title: coconut pies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until mixed well.
Add margarine and other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown on top or until done. Makes 2 pies.
I sprinkle coconut on top of pie before putting in oven.
But use most of the coconut in pie filling.

title: smoked sausage vegetable dinner
directions: Cut sausage into 1/2-inch slices.
Wash potatoes and peel, then cut into slices or quarters.
Layer sausage, potatoes and next 3 ingredients in a large Dutch oven, sprinkling each vegetable layer with salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup water and bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 35 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: almond rice casserole
directions: Boil soup in water.
Brown meat, rice, peppers and onions lightly.
Mix in celery and add to soup with almonds.
Bake
at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry dessert - can be used as a salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Set in refrigerator overnight.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients and add sweet milk (I use 2%) to fill the gallon container.
Freeze (in crank or electric).
You may use chocolate syrup if you desire chocolate flavor.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In food processor, cream the cheese, mayonnaise, onion, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add shrimp and process gently. You want small chunks of shrimp.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn casserole
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until lightly browned.
Remove and set aside.
Pour 1/4 cup of bacon drippings over bread crumbs; set aside.
Save 2 tablespoons of remaining drippings in pan; saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in corn and bacon. Spoon into a 1-quart baking dish; sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly and heated through. Serves 6 to 8.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
