Combine in a bowl cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda and egg.
Mix all these ingredients, then add yeast.
Add flour.
Form into ball and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and put into well-greased casserole, 1 1/2 to 2-quart size.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Brush top with butter and sprinkle with salt if desired.

title: easy chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Spread a tablespoon of enchilada sauce on each tortilla. Fill with chicken, onion and peppers and roll up. Spray casserole dish with a nonstick spray, then cover with 3 to 4 tablespoons of enchilada sauce. Place enchiladas in casserole dish and pour rest of enchilada sauce over them. Sprinkle cheese over enchilada sauce and place olives on top. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes. I use nonstick aluminum foil to cover while cooking.

title: asparagus with mustard sauce
directions: Cook a handful of asparagus in boiling water for 10 minutes. Melt butter and stir in flour.
Stir in mayonnaise and mustard. Season with favorite seasoning.
Pour over asparagus and enjoy.

title: mix vegetable curry
directions: Heat a sauce pan on high heat.
Put some oil in it.
Add onions and cook on med heat until lightly brown and until the oil separates.
Add tomatoes and mix vegetable and cook until tender and oil comes on top.

title: eulane mccurry's layered salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; add fruit cocktail and congeal.
Mix 3 cups cold milk with vanilla pudding mix; beat for 2 minutes.
Put over congealed strawberry Jell-O. Mix pistachio pudding with 2 cups pineapple juice from drained pineapple.
Beat 2 minutes and spread over vanilla pudding. Spread crushed pineapple (drained) over the pistachio pudding. Cover with Cool Whip and put sliced peaches on top.

title: spiced shrimp
directions: Cover frozen shrimp with warm water for about 5 minutes.
Pull apart and rinse with cold water.
Place all ingredients except shrimp in a large pan.
Let boil for about 5 minutes and reduce heat.
Add shrimp and cook for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Pour through colander to drain.
Can be put back on stove to keep warm.

title: spicy pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Combine in small bowl.
Beat until light and fluffy, then frost cake.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: You will need a brown grocery bag (clean).

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; let stand for 30 minutes.
Then mix eggs.
Blend together and bake in hot water pan for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, until ingredients are well mixed.
Alternate flour and orange juice, ending with flour.
Pour in a tube pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: addie's cole slaw dessert
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, milk and mustard together well.
Then mix with same amount of mayonnaise.
Pour over shredded cabbage.

title: pizza dough
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixing bowl, combine 2 cups flour yeast and salt.
Stir in water, egg and oil.
Beat at low speed with electric mixer for 1/2 minutes scraping sides.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand stir enough flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Put onto floured surface and knead until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Place into greased bowl, turning once. Cover and let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Divide dough in two greased 9x9x2 baking pans for sicilian or 2 round 12-14 inch pizza pans.
Pat out on pans.
Sicilian let stand 30 minutes. Regular top immediately with desired toppings.
Bake for 25 minutes.
(Before putting pizza dough on pans, you can sprinkle with cornmeal).

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add strawberries, oil and sugar.
Mix all dry ingredients and slowly add strawberry mix.
Pour into loaf pans or muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (until done).

title: exotic luncheon salad
directions: Cook turkey breast; cut up.
Combine turkey, grapes, water chestnuts and celery.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to turkey mixture.
Garnish with pineapple chunks.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: lu's punch
directions: Mix 70% fruit juices, 30% sparkling water and crushed ice.

title: peach apple jam
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Cook slowly until thick and transparent, about 1 hour, stirring often.
Ladle into hot jars; seal.
Makes 2 pints.

title: onion rice
directions: In this order place in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Place tight-fitting lid on pan.
Turn down fire as low as possible without it going out and simmer for approximately 18 to 20 minutes.
Quickly remove lid.
Spoon out small amount.
Replace lid, tasting rice for doneness.
When done, remove from heat. Rice will have absorbed beef stock and all the onions will be layered on top.
Use as side dish or with gravy on top.
To this dish you could add browned ground beef or small cubed beef tips, cooked to serve as one dish meal.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix together.
Use for sandwich spread or serve with crackers.

title: hamburger potato pie
directions: Brown the chopped onion in butter.
Remove onion and brown ground beef with salt and pepper.
Place ground beef and onions, peas, tomatoes and catsup in a casserole to combine.
Mash potatoes, beat in 1 egg and spoon potatoes on top of other mixture.
Brown in 375° oven until peaks are golden.

title: chocolate pecan clusters
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients in large saucepan over low flame. Remove from heat.
Stir peanuts until thoroughly coated.
Drop from teaspoon on waxed paper.
Cool until firm.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: aunt grace's salad dressing
directions: Whirl all ingredients in blender for 1 minute.
Stores well in refrigerator.
Quick, easy and delicious!

title: fudgy philly brownies
directions: Mix cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar until blended well.
Blend in 1 egg.
Melt margarine with chocolate over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Add remaining sugar, 3 eggs and vanilla to chocolate mixture; mix until well blended.
Add flour and mix well.
Reserve 1/2 cup chocolate batter.
Spread remaining batter into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture evenly over the chocolate batter.
Top with the reserved chocolate batter.
Cut through batter several times for a marbled effect.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into about 2 dozen bars.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients with mixer on low. Bake at 350° in muffin pan approximately 20 minutes.

title: shirley's "sausage" rice casserole
directions: Add sausage and seasoning to ground beef.
Brown in skillet; drain off the fat.
Add celery, pepper, onion, rice and 1 cup water.
Cook at 350° until almost dry in uncovered casserole dish.

title: chicken stuffed tomatoes
directions: Saute chicken in butter until tender (about 5 minutes).
Cut thin slice from tops of tomatoes.
Scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Dice tomato tops and pulp; drain.
Combine all ingredients except tomato shells.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into shells.
Serve on lettuce garnished with avocado wedges and ripe olives if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese on the hoof
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Chop beef and peppers.
Add to cheese mixture.
Pinch out middle of bread, leave sides and bottom. Cook cheese mixture at 325° for about 45 minutes in casserole dish.
Remove and place in bread bowl.
Cook for additional 15 to 20 minutes or until bread starts browning. Serve with Fritos.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Heat oil and fry onion and green pepper until both are soft. Defrost okra and add to onion and green pepper.
Add tomatoes. Cook until thick.
"This may be served over rice."

title: green bean casserole
directions: Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use a little French fried onions on top of dish and bake 5 minutes more.

title: white cloud
directions: Cook rice in water using your favorite recipe or cook in tightly covered pot for 20 minutes.
Set aside.

title: low-fat taco soup
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon low-fat oleo.
Brown turkey and drain.
Mix all ingredients in large pan and bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes.

title: strawberry goodie good
directions: Stir all ingredients together and freeze.
Yum!

title: filbert christmas cookies
directions: Chop nuts fine with food processor; soften butter.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Mix together all ingredients.
Roll between sheets of waxed paper.
Chill if dough gets sticky.
Don't add more flour.
A little powdered sugar will do.
Cut in fancy shapes.
Bake 12 minutes at 300° to a light brown.
Cool and decorate with pink and green icing.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Make into balls, roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bena kirkscey's truly different cupcakes
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine and chocolate.
Add butter flavoring and nuts.
In bowl, mix flour, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Combine the 2 mixtures with spoon.
Do not beat.
Fill lined cupcake tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 16 (2-inch) cupcakes.

title: hungry person's salad
directions: Wash both lettuce and tomatoes.
Shake lettuce to remove excess water.
Cut lettuce (romaine) in bite size pieces or tear (iceberg lettuce), as desired.
Cut tomatoes in wedge shape and throw in lettuce.
Cut meat and cheese in slivers to taste.
Peel eggs, rinse and cut in wedges.
Toss with two forks and eat. Serves 5 people.

title: curried rice salad
directions: In large bowl, combine the rice, green pepper, onion, celery, radishes and pickle relish.
Mix well.
In small bowl, combine mayonnaise and spices. Stir to blend flavors. Add the mayonnaise to the rice mixture and mix well.
Chill for several hours. Serves 8.

title: basic cobbler
directions: On bottom of baking dish, spread a layer of sweetened fruit (apples, peaches, cherries), then a layer of pastry.
Then spread another layer of fruit and top off with a layer of pastry.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes, checking frequently.

title: grandma's chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in deep casserole dish.
Add soup, broth, margarine and rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 400°.

title: homestyle macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni with pinch of salt until tender, then drain. Stir in margarine.
Mix together the milk, egg, salt and pepper. Fold in macaroni along with 1 cup cheese.
Stir well.
Add pimentos if desired.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup grated cheese. Dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: grandma bea's strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch and cook over medium-high heat until it's thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add the food coloring and lemon juice.
Mix together and let cool.
Add the strawberries and pour into a baked crust.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Pat into 4 rolls.
Freeze (wrap in wax paper, then in foil).
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 325° until light brown (about 7 minutes).
You can use less nuts and add coconut or black walnuts.
Also, you can mix 2 tablespoons cocoa, 2 chopped apples and 3/4 cup raisins to all or part of the dough.

title: dirty cake
directions: Mix and spread over the cookie mixture.
Sprinkle the rest of the cookie mixture on top of pudding.
Chill.

title: gary mcintosh spinach & ham quiche
directions: Mix and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes then 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pilgram pumpkin bars and frosting
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9-inch square pan. Beat together eggs, 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup sugar, oil and pumpkin.
In a separate bowl mix together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir well.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Pour into pan and bake for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together margarine, vanilla, powdered sugar and hot water until creamy.
Spread over cool cake.
Cut into bars and refrigerate.

title: pretzels
directions: In a large bowl, mix yeast in water.
Stir in sugar.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
Stir until dough no longer sticks to the sides of the bowl.
Knead on floured board for 5 minutes.
Divide dough into 16 balls.
Roll balls into "snakes" 12 inches long and make shapes. Place pretzels on a well greased cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg white and sprinkle with kosher salt.

title: cajun rump roast
directions: Make several deep slits in top and sides of roast with a paring knife.
Fill slits with garlic cloves and green onions. Rub roast with salt and red cayenne pepper.
Place in a large cooking bag that is in a large shallow oblong pan.
Place peeled potatoes, carrots and mushrooms around roast.
On top of roast, sprinkle 1/2 green onions, parsley and mint.
Mix wine, water, bitters and soy; pour around roast.
Seal bag; poke with holes. Bake 2 hours or so at 325° until done.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until very limp.
Put 1/2 onions in casserole.	Sprinkle
with	1/2
crackers and cheese.
Add remainder of onions, cheese and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; crumble potato chips or crumbled buttered Ritz crackers over top and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes for 150
directions: Arrange potato slices in 4 large metal baking pans.
Sprinkle each with salt and pepper, each layer.
Add chopped onion.
Pour a quart of water over each pan.
Cover and bake in 425° oven that has been preheated.
Turn oven to 375°; bake about 30 minutes.
Mix 1 cup flour with each can of soup; pour over each pan.
Bake uncovered for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: orange nut cake
directions: Mix all of these together in a large mixing bowl.
Beat 1 minute on low
and	5
minutes
on high.
Pour 1 cup chopped pecans into bottom	of tube pan.
Pour batter over nuts.
Bake 60 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: baked limas
directions: Top with bacon.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
It can be frozen after baking.

title: nacho skillet casserole
directions: In large skillet, brown beef; add onion and green pepper. Cook and drain well.
Stir in sugar, oregano, chili powder, kidney beans, tomato sauce and corn.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until most of moisture is absorbed.
Sprinkle tortilla chips evenly over meat mixture; top with cheese.
Cover and simmer 3 or 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: turkey stew with dumplings
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan or Dutch oven over medium heat.
Add onion and celery; cook, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender.
Add turkey, cabbage, tomatoes, beans, broth, thyme and salt.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add macaroni.
Stir to coat and brown slightly.
Add beef and brown.
Stir in tomato juice or sauce. Bring to boil.
Mix in next 4 ingredients and salt and pepper. Transfer to 9 x 13-inch pan (can freeze for 1 month).
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered 10 minutes.

title: nut cake
directions: Melt oleo.
Beat eggs.
Add to oleo.
Add syrup and orange juice.
Mix flour over nuts, sugar and spices.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in slowest oven possible for 3 hours; do not preheat oven.
Test with straw.

title: chicken breast with long grain and wild rice
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Heat oven to 325°.
Melt the oleo in the casserole.
Place the chicken in dish and turn over in the oleo.
Sprinkle very lightly with salt. Cover with bell pepper, onion and celery.
Cover dish with lid or foil and bake for 45 minutes.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all.
Pour into pie shells. Chill overnight.
Eat and enjoy.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soda crackers. Heat until boiling. Crush crackers in unbaked pie crust and pour over this the boiling mixture. Dot with butter. Add a top unbaked crust and bake until crusts are brown in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. This will taste just like apple pie.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Butter a 9 or 10-inch dish, 1/2-inch deep.
Place peaches in dish.
Spread bread cubes evenly over peaches.
Mix butter, sugar, flour and egg together.
Pour evenly over bread, making sure all bread is covered.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Scald milk.
Add and stir until dissolved the sugar, butter and salt.
Sprinkle yeast over water. Add to milk mixture when milk has cooled to lukewarm.
Beat in egg.
Sift flour.
Stir in part of the flour and knead in the remainder.
Use more flour if necessary to form a dough that can be handled easily.
Place in greased bowl; brush top with melted butter.
Cover and let dough rise in a warm place until doubled in bulk.
Punch down and roll out about 3/8-inch thick; cut into rounds with floured biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted butter; fold over and brush again with butter.
Allow to rise again in a warm place until light, about 35 minutes.
Bake in preheated 425° oven about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Combine evaporated milk and meat.
Divide into 5 patties on waxed paper. Pat each into a 6-inch circle.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing mix into center of each patty.
Draw meat over stuffing and seal.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole; do not stack.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: aunt cashie's fruit cake
directions: Sift the following ingredients together:
white flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add and mix well pecans, pineapple, cherries and white raisins.
Then cream together butter gradually with white sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one by one, beating well after each.
Add brandy (She never did; I do). Add all together.
Be sure to completely mix.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan or 2 loaf pans (bread) at 275° for 2 3/4 to 3 hours.
Place shallow pan of water in oven to keep cake moist.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until thick, medium to low heat. Let cool, add butter and vanilla.
Pour into cooked pie shell. Top with meringue.

title: spanish omelette(huevos a la mexicana)
directions: Mix eggs with milk.
Add onion and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook in a greased pan until bottom is hard; fold and cook a few minutes more.

title: mystery salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice to piping hot. Add jello and mix well. Cool completely. Add buttermilk and mix real good.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Chill. Will last a week.

title: pork roast with herbed rub
directions: Pat pork dry with paper towel. In small bowl, combine all rub ingredients well and apply to all surfaces of the pork roast. Place roast in a shallow pan and roast in 350 degree oven for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until internal temperature is 155 degrees. Remove from oven and let rest for 5 to 10 minutes before slicing.

title: horse show ham
directions: Slice and trim ham. Alternate ham and sauce in roaster.
Bake at 350°
for 3 hours.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix and eggs together, will be crumbly.
In separate bowl mix pudding mix and milk. Combine the two mixes and fold in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in tube pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and melt butter in baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and pour into dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pauline's pleasantville crab cakes
directions: Refrigerate mixture for 24 hours.
When ready to cook crab cakes, have the following items ready:
bread crumbs, an egg wash, and hot oil.
Saltine crackers crushed with a rolling pin may be substituted for bread crumbs.
For an egg wash, beat two eggs in a cup of milk.
Make crab mixture into balls or cakes.
Dip in egg wash.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Deep fry to golden brown.
Enjoy, enjoy, enjoy!

title: savory pot roast
directions: In 6-quart saucepan, in hot oil, brown roast on all sides. Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and one cup water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover.
Cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover.
Cook 45 minutes or until roast is fork tender.

title: christmas fruit drops
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: *Set aside handful stuffing for top.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, sifting the soda with the flour before adding it.
Bake in a moderate oven (350° to 375°) in a greased shallow pan or in muffin tins.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: turkey casserole(microwave)
directions: Microwave:
Combine all ingredients except crackers and margarine in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook for 15 to 17 minutes on 80% power or until heated through.
Toss margarine and crackers on top of dish.
Heat 1 minute on High.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Crush crackers. In a large bowl, mix the meat, onions, crushed crackers and seasonings. Shape into meatballs. Fry in oil until done. Remove and drain off excess oil.

title: russian borscht
directions: Fill large kettle with water.
Add soup bones or rib bones if you prefer more meat.
Add onion, beef broth cubes and spices.
Let boil and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Add tomato sauce.
Remove bones and take off meat and return meat to kettle.
Add carrots and celery.
When almost done, add potatoes and cabbage.
Add canned beets last.
I use canned because the fresh turns potatoes and cabbage red.
When serving, add heaping spoonful of sour cream in each bowl.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup and margarine.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Lower oven temperature to 250° and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Blend together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add oats, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Dough is crumbly.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Bring to boil the water, sugar and cornstarch.
Add the Jell-O and stir to dissolve.
Let cool.
Pour over about 1 quart berries. Stir to cover all berries and pour in baked pie shell. Refrigerate.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: coconut pecan chess pie
directions: Beat eggs with fork; add next 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Put in pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then reduce heat and bake for 30 minutes.

title: squash biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in a little water.
Add to the squash the sugar and the softened butter.
Beat well, then turn in yeast; beat once more.
Add sifted flour and stir well with a spoon. Add enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Leave in warm place overnight.
Then turn into greased gem
pans and bake in a hot oven.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters, roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture and place in a Bundt pan.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and 1/2 cup cinnamon and sugar and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° about 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Let cool.

title: mary's tortilla chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts or bake with skin side up.
Bone and cube breasts into a large 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with corn tortillas cut into 4 strips.
Combine next 6 ingredients and pour over chicken and tortilla strips.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, covered.
Then finish, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add egg yolks to water; lightly mix and add to butter/sugar mixture.
Add flour gradually and combine completely.
Separate dough into four sections and form each into a roll about an inch and a half in diameter.
Wrap each roll in wax paper and refrigerate at least overnight.
Slice each roll about 1/4-inch; place on cookie sheet.
Paint each slice with a glaze of egg white, mixed with ground nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: catsup and onions
directions: Mix tomatoes and tomato paste together.

title: pride of iowa cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs.
Sift and add the flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 375°.
Makes about 5 dozen.
Freezes well.

title: sunrise delight pie
directions: Beat sugar and cream cheese together until smooth.
Add 1/2 of the can of pie filling and the can of crushed pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Use pineapple chunks around the outer rim of the pie to form a circular dam.
Pour the other 1/2 of the cherry pie filling in the center.
Refrigerate until firm. Cherry pie filling can be substituted with strawberry or other flavored filling.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine egg, tomato sauce, bread crumbs, parsley, oregano, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add ground beef, mixing well. Place meat on foil.
Shape into 7 x 9-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle salami on top.
Sprinkle cheese over salami, leaving a narrow margin around edges.
Roll meat, jelly roll fashion, starting from 7-inch end, using foil to help you roll.
Press to seal edges. Place meat loaf, seam side down, in greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until done.

title: chicken with apricot sauce
directions: Dip chicken in milk, then into graham cracker crumbs.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix jam, dressing and soup mix together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream oleo and blend in 2 cups sugar until real creamy.
Add 6 eggs, beating well.
Add crushed wafers.
Add 1/2 cup milk.
Mix well.
Fold in coconut and pecans.
Grease and flour a tube pan and pour in batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: perfect scalloped oysters
directions: Drain oysters, saving liquor.
Combine crumbs, margarine, salt and pepper.
Spread 1/3 of the buttered crumbs in greased 8 x 1 1/4-inch round baking dish.
Cover with half the oysters.
Using another third of the crumbs, spread a second layer; cover with remaining oysters.	Combine cream, oyster liquor and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over oysters.
Top with last of crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.	Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry freeze
directions: Mix and freeze. Eat and enjoy.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients slowly in double boiler until tender. Beat together the remaining ingredients and add to cooked rice.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese warm to room temperature.
Beat cream cheese, marshmallow cream and orange juice together.
Mixture will liquify.
Refrigerate to firm dip.
Serve with seasonal fruit.

title: cream cheese braid
directions: Stir in 1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup butter. Cool to lukewarm.
In large bowl, sprinkle 2 packages yeast over 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add sour cream mixture and 2 beaten eggs. Gradually add 4 cups flour.
Mix well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours. (I add the first 2 cups of flour with an electric hand mixer, then the last 2 cups by hand.)

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together milk, Cool Whip and lemonade real good and spread in two graham cracker pie crusts or one 9 x 12-inch crust. Refrigerate.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll dough into 6-inch circles.
Place diced apples in center. Add dot of butter and dash of cinnamon.
Pull edges together at top and pinch together.
Place in greased baking dish.
Make syrup of sugar and water by bringing to a boil. Pour over dumplings. Bake at 350° until golden brown and apples are tender.
Good served with vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Separate the eggs.
Mix the
yolks,
milk and sugar with beater in bowl.
Beat egg whites
and
add
to
mixture and add vanilla.
Mix all ingredients together;
pour in an unbaked pie shell and bake in oven at 350° and bake until pie sets.

title: jimmy carter dessert
directions: Blend together and press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Cool.

title: truffles
directions: In a saucepan, melt chips and milk.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Chill for 2 hours, until firm.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in various coatings, i.e., sprinkles, cocoa or chopped nuts. Chill 1 or more hours.
Store in airtight container.

title: nut tree chess pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
In small bowl, beat eggs with fork.
Add milk and butter.
Mix well with dry ingredients.
Bake in slow oven (275°) for 2 hours.
Serve with whipping cream.

title: jt finger cookies
directions: Line 15 X 10 X 1 inch cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Spray well with non-stick cooking spray.
Place crackers in a single layer on sheet.
(Cover entire sheet with no holes.)
In a small saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add sugar; bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour evenly over crackers.
Bake at 350 for 10-12 minutes or until browned. Immediately after removing from oven, sprinkle chocolate chips over crackers.
Spread melted chocolate into even layer over crackers.
Sprinkle nuts over the top while chocolate is still melted.
After allowing to cool completely, you should be able to pick up the candy in one piece.
Remove foil and into 1 to 2 inch pieces.

title: best ever cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl; add eggs already beaten.
Mix well with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash potatoes; remove eyes.
Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Fry on oiled skillet until brown.
Serve with applesauce with cinnamon added.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Steam vegetables until thawed.
Add water chestnuts, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Mix well.
Pour in casserole dish.
Mix crackers and margarine.
Pour over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, until top is brown.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage, pepper, celery and onion; drain well.
Mix with other ingredients, saving some of the cheese to sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mom's tomato sauce
directions: Puree tomatoes in blender.
Combine puree with can of tomato sauce and 1/2 can of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients, lower heat and simmer on low for 4 hours.

title: farina delight
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and gradually add next 6 ingredients.
Beat the 6 egg whites until stiff and fold into first mixture.
Place batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Take from oven while hot (it will look like it flopped).
Break up into pieces in a bowl.
When cold, place pieces on a large cake plate alternating with layers of whipped cream. Form into a mound shape and cover with whipped cream.
Decorate with cherry halves.
Place in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: cherry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and lightly packed brown sugar; add beaten egg and beat well.
Blend or sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine milk and syrup from red maraschino cherries.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternating with milk mixture.
Combine after each addition but do not beat.
Carefully fold in drained, quartered red maraschino cherries, and chopped walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: paprika chicken halves
directions: Boil chicken for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from water; mix butter with salt, paprika and garlic.
Brush chicken with this mixture using about half of it.
Put chicken on grill.
Grill chicken turning once.
Keep basting chicken with rest of mixture. When chicken is about done, brush on barbecue sauce.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Heat one inch of salt water (1/2 teaspoon to every cup water) to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool.
Fry bacon until crisp. Drain bacon on paper towels.
Cook onion in bacon fat until tender.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil one minute, then remove from heat. Crumble bacon into mixture.
Toss into potatoes until coated.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix ingredients and put in buttered casserole dish.
Set in pan with hot water.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat with diced onion, celery and bell pepper.
Add gravy and soup.
Mix.
In deep casserole, put potatoes on bottom; spread meat mixture on top; sprinkle with cheese; bake at 350° until cheese melts or until hot!
Cut in squares and serve with salad and veggies.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into hot greased cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.

title: golden puffs
directions: Note:
May add chopped apple pieces or applesauce.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Pour over meat and bake till chicken is done.
Serve with rice.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Add butter, eggs, and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Place on sides and bottom of 10-inch pie pan.
Spoon cottage cheese over spaghetti.
Add hamburger to spaghetti sauce and pour into shell.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil; bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and bake additional 5 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(I usually double the recipe.)

title: sicilian olive salad(insalata di olivi schiacciati)
directions: Slice celery into pieces about 1/4-inch thick.
Add olives, onion, salt, pepper, oregano, oil and vinegar.
Mix well and allow to chill about 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cut and cube 4 bread slices in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken, pepper, celery, mayo, onion, salt and pepper and spread over bread cubes.
Lay other bread cubes or slices on top.
Beat egg and milk together and pour over mixture.
Chill overnight in fridge.

title: hot clam and cheddar dip(makes 4 cups)
directions: Saute onion, celery, carrots and garlic in oil in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in dry milk, flour and pepper. Drain clams; reserve juice.
Add water to juice to make 2 1/2 cups.
Gradually add juice mixture to flour mixture in saucepan. Return to heat.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture just comes to a boil and thickens.
Stir in clams, cheese, mustard and hot pepper sauce.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese melts. Keep warm.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In bottom of 9 x 13 pan, spray with cooking spray. Will not stick if you use this. Spread the coconut in pan, then spread the pecans on the coconut. Mix cake mix by directions on the package and spread over the pecans. Mix cream cheese, oleo and sugar; mix until smooth and creamy. Add this over cake mix as best you can; it will be stiff. Bake at 350° until tests done, but do not overcook. This is rich and delicious.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Gradually add water, stirring with fork.
Dough will be crumbly.
Turn out on a floured surface; knead until smooth and form into ball.
Divide in half.
Let dough stand 10 minutes.
Roll each half into 12 1/2 x 10-inch rectangle. Cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Do not roll or repatch!
Fry each in deep fryer until golden brown.

title: date nut bars
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, except powdered sugar.
Bake in cake pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into bars; shake in powdered sugar.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Place toast on cookie sheet or in shallow baking pan.
Spread with tuna.
Top with onion and egg.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over open-faced sandwiches.
Broil until hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meringue(topping for pies)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a mixer bowl, put egg whites. Be careful there is no yolk in egg whites; this will prevent the whites from beating into stiff peaks. Beat egg whites on high speed until foamy. Gradually add sugar, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla. Continue to beat on high speed until whites stand in peaks. Spread on top of pie filling. Be sure to seal crust edge with meringue to prevent shrinkage. Bake until meringue is lightly brown (watch closely), 5 to 10 minutes. Cool pie on wire rack. Makes meringue for 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Crush
crackers.
Beat egg whites very stiff.
Mix well and fold
in
pecans.
Put in 9-inch greased pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes
in a 350° oven on top shelf.
Let cool and top with whipped cream.
Let stand in refrigerator 3 hours before serving. (Makes its own crust).

title: peppi pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; slice pepperoni into halves or strips.
In large glass or plastic bowl, combine pasta, pepperoni, artichoke hearts, olives and green onion; add salad dressing, tossing to coat all ingredients.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Stir and bake an additional 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green enchiladas casserole
directions: Mix green chiles, soup and cup of milk together.
Line corn chips in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour mixture over corn chips. Sprinkle shredded cheese over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; roll into small balls. Chill.
Melt paraffin.
Add chocolate chips, stirring until chips melt.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Place on a plate.
Cool. Makes 75 to 80 pieces.

title: autumn soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook and stir chopped onion with meat until onion is tender. Stir in carrots, celery, potatoes, salt, bottled brown sauce (Worcestershire sauce) and rest of the ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Toss noodles with butter.
Place noodles in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer sauerkraut, corned beef and tomatoes.
Dot with salad dressing; sprinkle cheese and top with crumbs and caraway seed.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fried corn
directions: Shuck corn.
Remove corn silk and wash each ear of corn.
Cut kernels off the corn, using the down stroke of a sharp knife to remove.
Then cut close to the cob again with knife's sharp edge. (This is referred to as cream-style cutting.)
Scrape juice out of the corn by passing the knife once more over the cob.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soups, melted butter, sherry and almonds.
Pour half into rice until moistened. Place chicken in rice and add rest of liquid on top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of that, then sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 275°
for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: lazy person's sweet pickles
directions: Drain dill pickles.
Slice thin and return to jar.
Bring vinegar and sugar to a hard boil and pour over sliced dills in jar.
Let stand until cool.
Refrigerate.
Best tasting sweet pickles you ever "worked hard for."

title: taco dip
directions: Cover with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in saucepan.
Stir continuously until sugar is dissolved.
Lower heat.
Cook without stirring until 300°.
Remove from heat.
Add food coloring and cinnamon oil.
Pour on buttered cooking sheet.
Cool completely. Crack into pieces.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: gooey butter dessert
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/2 cup margarine and 1 egg in bowl; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine 2 eggs, cream cheese, remaining 1/2 cup margarine and confectioners sugar in bowl; mix until smooth.
Spoon evenly into prepared dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Yield:
15 servings.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add vanilla and chocolate. Blend until thick.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream.
Chill.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients. Leave dough sticky (slightly), rather than dry, even if it means using less flour.
Lift dough out of bowl and put a few drops of oil in bowl.
Return the dough and turn it around in the oil and then right side up so oil is on the top.
Cover with a dish towel and let rise until double in size.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Brown chops.
Put aside.
Place 1 cup rice in greased casserole with dry onion soup mix.
Add 2 to 2 1/2 cups of water. Place chops on top.
Place green pepper ring on each chop.
Fill ring with chili sauce.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 300°.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Heat butter in large skillet or griddle.
Pour 1/4 cup batter into skillet; cook until light brown.
Flip; cook second side.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 10 pancakes.
Total cooking time: 5 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Mix margarine and flour.
Add milk and sliced potatoes in greased pan.
Chop half the onions over the potatoes. Add the rest of the potatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour mixture of margarine, flour and milk over potatoes. Cook in medium hot oven at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: pizza salad
directions: Spread rolls very flat, pressing seams together on cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions on container until brown; cool.
Cream cream cheese with Ranch style dressing.
Spread over dough.
Add your cut vegetables and sprinkle over the cheese spread.
Serve immediately.
Yum! Yum!

title: chocolate decadence
directions: Prepare a 9-inch cake pan by placing parchment paper in the bottom (cut to fit) and then buttering and flouring pan.
In a saucepan, gently heat eggs with sugar until lukewarm (be very careful not to overheat as eggs will "scramble").

In a separate saucepan, melt bittersweet chocolate with unsalted butter. Combine egg mixture with butter by first folding 1/4 of the egg into the chocolate, then folding the additional chocolate into the egg mixture.
Add flour until just combined.
Pour into pan. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight or freeze for two hours.
Remove from refrigerator or freezer about 15 minutes before serving.
Serve in small wedges with raspberry sauce (pureed raspberries either plain or with lemon and a bit of sugar) and a dollop of unsweetened whipped cream.
Serves 8 to 10 polite people or 6 chocoholics.

title: pink salad
directions: Fold together and chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: onion baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into large pieces (don't peel).
Place in a large Ziploc bag.
Add cooking oil and Lipton soup. Shake. Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir occasionally. Serve hot!
Delicious!

title: microwave rice pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine milk, rice, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until rice is tender, about 25 minutes.
Add the eggs and cook an additional 3 minutes.
Add cream and vanilla.

title: pico de gallo(fresh vegetable relish)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a glass bowl. (Do not use metal when working with peppers because acid bleaches aluminum or tin from the pans.)
Place in refrigerator for several hours. Stir occasionally in order to coat all vegetables.
Serve with corn chips.
Especially good with blue corn chips.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Cook until onions are tender.
Remove from heat.
Brown ground beef; drain. Add 1 1/2 cups water, bouillon cubes, ketchup and garlic salt. Cook over low heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix 1/4 cup water and flour; mix well.
Stir into meat mixture.
Will thicken fast. If too thick, add a little water.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Heat to a boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: autumn salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add jello; stir until dissolved. Add cream
cheese;
stir.
Cool.
Fold in apples, nuts, celery and Cool
Whip.
Pour
into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: brown sugar chocolate cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, shortening and egg.
Sift together salt, soda and flour.
Add the two mixes together with 1/2 cup milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a cookie sheet and bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Remove promptly when done.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook roast, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours; do not overcook or meat will be tough.
Chill roast at least 2 hours. Save pan juices, skimming fat.
Combine pan
juices, beef broth, water, garlic, oregano, red pepper and black pepper in 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add thinly sliced roast and green peppers.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve on hot hoagie buns.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center of mix. Beat eggs and oil well and add to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in strawberries, pecans and food coloring.
Divide into 2 greased 8-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Leave in pan for 20 minutes.
Remove, wrap and let stand overnight before slicing.

title: vegetarian manicotti
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until transparent.
Add tomatoes, basil and sugar (this is optional) and salt.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours.

title: crunchy chinese salad
directions: Chop cabbage, bell pepper and green onions, place in large bowl and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Beat butter until smooth and creamy.
Beat sugar in gradually until fluffy.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Beat 3 minutes after each addition.
Spread filling in a pie shell, chill 2 hours or until pie shell is firm.
Spread Cool Whip over chilled filling.
Sprinkle pecans over pie.
Serve chilled.

title: shrimp and cheese pastries
directions: Stir together cream cheese, shrimp, horseradish and Tabasco. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Roll out puff pastry on a lightly floured surface into a 16 x 8-inch rectangle.
Spread filling lengthwise over a 14 x 3-inch area in the center of pastry and transfer to a buttered baking sheet.
Brush edges with milk.
Fold the ends over filling and fold the long sides over the filling, overlapping them slightly.
Brush top with remaining milk and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, slice into strips or triangles.
Serves 5 to 10 persons.

title: smoked boneless shoulder butt and cabbage dish
directions: In the morning place cabbage which has been cut in half and stalks removed, in a pan of cold water.

title: christmas bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add evaporated milk, sugar, shortening, salt and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in fruit and enough remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Do not knead.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled in size, about 1 1/4 hours.
Punch down.
Turn onto a floured surface; knead 3 to 4 minutes.
Pat evenly into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until nearly double in size, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from pan to cool on a wire rack.
Combine confectioners sugar,
milk and vanilla; drizzle over bread.
Garnish with candied fruit, if desired.
Servings: 1.

title: julie's mazola cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquid; mix and bake in 9 x 13-inch baking pan for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix margarine,
sugar,
syrup
and
salt in a saucepan. Bring to a
boil and cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Stir well.
Pour over popped corn, to which the nuts have
been
added.
Mix
well.
Place in a large flat pan and bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
When cool enough to handle, break into pieces.

title: swedish yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in small
amount
of
warm water and add remaining ingredients.
Set to
rise.
When
ready,
roll
out inch thick.
Cut with
biscuit cutter.
Put small piece butter on one side and fold in halves.
Put in pan 1 inch apart.
Let rise. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Boil lasagna noodles; drain.
Brown meat; drain.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot; cook on low for 3 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll crescent rolls onto cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Flatten out into one large roll.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool.
Spread dip of your choice onto dough. Place chopped vegetables on dip.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours. Cut into squares or pizza slices.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients until fluffy, then add eggs.
Add flour and lemon extract.
Spread into greased 11 x 19-inch or larger pan.
Cut surface of batter (prior to baking) into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Take one tablespoonful of cherry pie filling into center of each square.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, just until barely browned on edges.
Do not overbake!

title: impossible bacon and broccoli pie
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer broccoli, bacon, onion and cheese in the baking pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour mixture over the layers.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan the pineapple and apple pie filling and shake ingredients down until even.
Spread box of cake mix over this; sprinkle coconut and nuts over cake mix.
Pour melted butter over all.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: portuguese sausage soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in oil until transparent.
Add tomatoes, tomato puree and sausage (chunks).
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaves and serve.

title: pineapple chiffon crunch
directions: Dissolve jello in water and set aside to set.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, lemon juice, pineapple and salt to slightly beaten egg yolks.
Cook over boiling water until consistency of custard.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to stiffly beaten egg whites.
Whip cream.
When jello thickens beat with egg beater; add custard.
Fold in egg whites and whipped cream.
Cover bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan with crisp wafers or graham crackers.
Save a tablespoon to sprinkle on top.
Set several hours.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in a tightly covered jar. Makes enough for 6 quarts.

title: enchilada chili
directions: Fry ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Dump beef into large saucepan.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bring to boil. Then simmer for 45 minutes.
For deeper flavor, add more chili to taste.
Fill tortillas as directed.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mid and boil
1 minute and pour over, 3 cups oatmeal, 1 cup nuts, 1 cup coconut.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: Cook noodles per package instructions.
Heat half and half; do not boil.
Add Parmesan.
Stir frequently, allowing cheese to melt.
Add salt, pepper and margarine.
Mix with cooked noodles and enjoy.
Great with salad and bread.
Serves 6 and only takes 20 minutes to prepare.

title: pistachio-pineapple delight
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into bowl.
Add the mix.
With a wire whisk, rotary beater or electric mixer at lowest speed, beat until
well
blended.
Fold in whipped topping and nuts. Pudding will be soft-set and ready to eat in 5 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: chicken curry
directions: Boil the fryer with onions, celery, salt and pepper.
Bone the chicken.
Simmer the package of coconut with the cup of milk, then set aside to cool.
Strain the coconut through cheesecloth.
Saute onions and garlic in butter, then add curry, cayenne and ginger; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add flour, coconut milk and chicken stock. Cook, stirring, until smooth and thick.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in chicken and 1/2 cup half and half.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot rice with condiments: raisins, peanuts, mango chutney, pineapple chunks and coconut.

title: baked barbecued meat balls
directions: Combine tomato soup with brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, onion, butter or oleo, vinegar and mustard.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Pour over meat balls in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: enchilada stack up
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and add all other ingredients (except tortillas, cheese and tomato juice).
Layer meat, tortillas and cheese in crock-pot.
Pour tomato juice around edges.
Cook on low for 4 to 6 hours.

title: round steak continental
directions: Brush steak all over with Kitchen Bouquet.
Heat oil in skillet; brown steak on both sides using moderate heat.
Combine and add remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, over low heat until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 2 greased coffee cans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: judy bush's olive dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Roll in nuts or nuts can be added to dip.
Refrigerate.

title: stay crisp slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill.
Soften gelatin in remaining 1/4 cup cold water.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir in gelatin.
Cool until thick. Beat well and add oil.
Drain vegetables.
Pour dressing over top. Mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Stir before serving.

title: versatile vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly and shake vigorously.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Boil water and add to jello.
Stir until jello is dissolved. Add cranberry sauce and cherry pie filling.
Whip with wire whip until foamy on top.
Chill until set.

title: grandma's brownies
directions: Grease a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix all ingredients until smooth.
When cool, frost with chocolate coffee icing.

title: beef and potato load
directions: Arrange evenly in greased, 2-quart baking dish, potatoes and 1 tablespoon cut-up onion, sprinkled with 1 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and parsley flakes.

title: krispie chicken
directions: Beat milk and mayonnaise.
Season chicken with seasonings. Dip fryer in milk mixture, then in crumbs.
Place in pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir in vanilla, raisins and coconut.
Place in buttered casserole dish.

title: texas black-eyed peas and rice
directions: Place peas, onion, water and salt in a large saucepan.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Add rice and continue simmering until rice is tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Cook bacon; remove from skillet.
Combine pea mixture, barbecue sauce, half of bacon, pepper and bacon drippings.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining bacon.
Bake in moderate oven approximately 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 large Texas servings.

title: natchez trace pasta
directions: Rinse beans, put in saucepan and cover with 2 cups cold water. Add bay leaf and 2 cloves garlic.
Bring to a boil over high heat and reduce to simmer.
Cook until tender, about 45 minutes.
Remove pot from heat.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo syrup and water together until it spins a thread (232° on candy thermometer).
Add peanuts; stir continuously.
Cook until it turns brownish gold (300°).
Take off heat; add butter, salt and soda.
Stir well.
Pour onto greased pans or plates to cool.
When cool, crack and store in airtight containers.

title: fish rolls or slices
directions: Mix well, then make in any shape you desire and fry in real hot fat or butter until brown.
Eat while hot.

title: day before breakfast
directions: Saute sausage; drain.
Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in dish.
Pour egg mixture on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Blend sugar and water in medium size pan and boil together until sugar forms heavy drops on top of spoon.
Remove from heat; stir in milk and butter.

title: skillet stuffed peppers
directions: While rice is cooking in medium skillet, brown beef until crumbly.
Drain.
Add onion.
Cook until onion is soft.
Remove from heat.
Mix in A.1., salt, pepper, tomato sauce, corn and rice.
Cut tops, seeds and membranes from peppers.
Discard. Fill peppers with meat and rice mixture.

title: fruit cake
directions: Reserve a slice of red and green pineapple and cherries to decorate cake.
In a large mixing bowl, mix all ingredients. Bake in tube cake pan.
Spray with Baker's Joy. Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: In mixing bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and mustard. Blend thoroughly with wire whisk.
Slowly pour in honey and lemon juice, continue mixing until smooth.

title: macadamia sour cream coffee cake
directions: Stir
the
soda
into the sour cream.
Blend the butter with 1 cup of sugar.
Add the sour cream and soda combination. Add
the vanilla;
mix
well.
Add
flour
sifted with baking powder.
Turn into
a
greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining sugar, cinnamon and chopped Macadamia nuts over all and marble them through the dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: beef roast
directions: Put roast into baking dish and spread steak sauce over roast. Sprinkle dry onion soup on top, then spoon golden mushroom soup over the dry soup.
Cover securely with foil and bake at 350° until tender.
(I find that a London Broil roast will be done in about 2 1/2 hours.
Other thicker roasts may require 3 to 4 hours.)

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Line a 10 x 13-inch dish with the toast.
Layer all other ingredients in the dish with some cheese with all layers.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over the ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375° until light brown; cut and serve for breakfast or snack.
Very good while warm.

title: holly wreaths
directions: In heavy, 2-quart saucepan, melt butter and marshmallows over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and food coloring and stir until well blended.
Fold in corn flakes.

title: caramels
directions: Melt butter; stir in sugar.
Stir in syrup.
Slowly add Eagle Brand, stirring constantly until it is in soft ball stage.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into buttered brownie pan.

title: green beans with garlic
directions: Cook beans in at least 4 quarts of salted, boiling water for 3 minutes or to taste.
They should remain a little crunchy.
Remove beans and immerse immediately in ice-cold water.
(This fixes the bright green color.)
Melt butter in saute pan; add garlic and thoroughly drained green beans.
Saute to warm beans and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Remove garlic.
Serve.

title: orange spice tea
directions: Mix well and store in tightly closed container.
Stir in heaping teaspoons in cup of boiling water.
Alter amount from 1 to 3 teaspoons to satisfy your own taste.

title: german "koch-kaese"(cooked cheese)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan and melt over low heat. Add 1/2 teaspoon ground red pepper (optional).
Stir constantly until melted.
Add milk and Swiss cheese, stirring constantly, and scrape bottom of pan to keep from sticking, until there are no lumps.
While hot, pour mixture into serving bowl and refrigerate. You can mix the old cheese and re-melt new batch.

title: shrimp ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Let stand while bringing soup to a boil.
Add cream cheese to soup and stir to dissolve.
Stir in gelatin (will be firming up by now).
Let cool for about 5 minutes.
Add all ingredients except shrimp.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let stand in refrigerator for another 5 minutes.
Add broken shrimp and pour into well-oiled mold. (Plastic or Tupperware molds may not need to be oiled.)
Tastes best if made the day before and allowed to season through.
Serve on Wheatsworth crackers and enjoy!!!

title: baked chicken squares
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter.
Add 4 tablespoons milk and beat until smooth.
Add chicken, seasoning, onion and cheese.
Separate biscuits and roll into 4-inch circle.
Spoon chicken mixture into middle of circle and pull edges up to seal.
Place in casserole dish that's been coated with nonstick spray.
Mix soup and 1 cup milk.
Pour over biscuits.	Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Make a very brown roux by cooking the flour in the oil, stirring to prevent burning.
Add chopped white onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Stir just until glazed.
Add water and let boil on low for 2 hours.
Add shrimp and cook for 30 minutes over high fire.
Add chopped onions, parsley and file.
Turn fire off and cover.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: sweet pickled watermelon
directions: Cook rind pieces in water with baking soda until tender. Drain off water.
Put rind in boiling syrup mixture and simmer for 40 minutes.

title: green chili quiche
directions: Mix layers in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: overnight vegetable salad
directions: Combine cabbage, peas, water chestnuts, onion, celery, apple and salt in a large bowl; toss well.

title: fruit soup
directions: For lower calories:
Use sugar-free jello and fruit packed in its own juice.
Tastes the same!)

title: cucumber and onion salad
directions: Combine vinegar, water, salt and sugar; mix thoroughly.
Pour over cucumbers, onion and scallions.
Mix and serve.

title: sherbet tropical punch
directions: Put frozen orange punch in a molder and refrigerate red punch and 7-Up to keep it cold.
Mix red punch and 7-Up in a punch bowl. Add frozen orange punch and Rainbow sherbet.

title: new mexico egg casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13 metal pan with Pam.
Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Line bottom of pan with two cans of the chiles.
Spread longhorn cheese over the chiles.
Cover with remaining two cans of chiles.
Spread Monterey Jack cheese over top.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
Beat yolks slightly with milk and seasonings.
Add yolks to whites; pour over layers of chile and cheese and smooth top.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until firm. Serves 12 for brunch.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw chopped spinach and drain until barely moist. In a bowl, combine spinach, soup mix, mayonnaise and sour cream. Mix thoroughly.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Cook bacon, drain and cut into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° for 30 minutes.
Bake until knife comes out clean.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar and blend in egg.
Add mixture to rest of ingredients.
Chill.

title: lebkuchen
directions: Combine brown sugar, honey and water in saucepan; bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Sift flour, salt, soda and spices together; combine with sugar mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Add eggs, fruits and almonds; mix well.
Shape into loaf; wrap in aluminum foil.
Place in refrigerator for 2 to 3 days to ripen.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness; cut into bars (1 x 3-inch).
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in moderate oven (350°).
When cool, spread with transparent icing made by adding boiling water to confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Yields 10 dozen cookies.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Chop pecans. Stir 1/2 pecans into mixture.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Top with remaining pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Blend in flour mixture and milk alternately, continuing to blend.
Add vanilla extract and blend until smooth.
Bake in a well-greased and floured tube pan at 350° until golden brown.

title: clam dip
directions: In a pot, mix clams (including juice), lemon juice, chopped onions, oregano, parsley, cloves and bread crumbs.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add Mozzarella cheese and pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: steak and mushroom pie
directions: Cube steak and slice mushrooms.
Place in loaf pan together with seasonings and gravy browning (use directions on packet). Cook in a 350° oven for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
(If you are in a hurry, you can use your microwave oven, but the slower method using the conventional oven allows the various flavors to blend together.)
When the meat, etc., is cooked, you can cover with pastry and bake in a hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Top with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: chicken spread
directions: In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, chicken and Italian dressing until well blended.
Spread on crackers and enjoy.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Fill a gallon container with sliced cucumbers.
Add salt and alum and fill with vinegar.
Soak in this solution for 6 weeks. Drain.
Pour sugar over cucumbers and stir around to mix.
Do not add any more vinegar.
Next, add pickling spices to the jar. Store and enjoy.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil in bowl.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes to thicken.
Heat oil to 375°.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into oil.
Cook about 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix biscuit mix with milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop dough by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Blend melted butter with garlic powder. Brush over warm biscuits.

title: easy tuna pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pie crust mix as directed on package for one crust pie.
Shape pastry into flattened square on lightly floured cloth-covered surface.
Roll pastry into 8-inch square.
Cut small slits in pastry.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour into ungreased square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Cover with pastry.
Bake about 35 minutes or until pastry is golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Crush Ritz crackers into fine bits.
Melt 1/2 stick of margarine and mix with crackers.
Place 1/2 of the crackers in bottom of casserole dish; cook broccoli according to directions. Melt cheese along with the other 1/2 margarine.
After broccoli is cooked, pour water off and stir in pan with cheese.
Pour in casserole dish and put remaining crackers on top.
Bake until brown.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Saute beef and onions in hot oil.
Place uncooked noodles on top of meat.
Mix remainder of ingredients and pour on top.
Press noodles down to moisten well.
Do not stir.
Bring to a boil, then turn heat on low.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini, celery and onion.
Combine and refrigerate; let stand overnight.
Next day, rinse zucchini, celery and onion with water.
Squeeze out very good.
Then put all the other ingredients together.
Cook; when zucchini comes to a boil, cook 30 minutes longer.
Put in clean Mason jars.
Seal lids.
Makes about 8 to 10 pints.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper; drain.
Add soups and picante sauce.
Put layer of meat mixture in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add a layer of grated cheese and then a good layer of broken tortilla chips.
Add remainder of meat mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: shrimp and artichoke casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt 4 1/2 tablespoons margarine and stir in flour.
When blended, add 3/4 cup milk and the cream gradually.
Stir constantly until mixture is smooth and thickened. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Arrange artichokes over the bottom of a buttered baking dish.
Scatter the shrimp over the artichokes.
Coat the mushrooms in remaining 2 tablespoons margarine for 6 minutes and spoon over shrimp and artichokes.
Add sherry and Worcestershire sauce to cream sauce and pour over contents of baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato puff balls
directions: Combine scalded milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm; add yeast.
Blend in eggs, mashed potatoes, then add flour and mix until dough is well blended.

Place in greased bowl; let rise until double in bulk, then turn out on floured board. Roll 1/2-inch thick; cut with biscuit cutter and let rise until light, then bake in hot oven 15 to 20 minutes until a golden brown.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix together and knead into balls.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: a million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large bowl, pecan pieces (as much as desired), pineapple, 1 tablespoon lemon juice and Cool Whip.
Stir up.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, sugar and salt together; set aside.
In another bowl, mix buttermilk, vegetable oil and eggs. Mix dry and liquid ingredients together slowly.
If too thick add more buttermilk.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Sift flour; measure.
Add salt; sift again.
Cream margarine and cream cheese well.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Fold in flour.
Bake in greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Let cool.
Add sugar, eggs and flour. Let rise until dough doubles in size.
Knead and cut out, put a dab of butter on top of rolls.
Let rise 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 325° in preheated oven until brown.

title: mamaw ethel's sour kraut
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cabbage, together. Stir until well dissolved and then add 2 additional cups of cold water. Pack cabbage into jars (not too tightly). Pour liquid over cabbage and seal.

title: meat loaf and sauce
directions: Brown hamburg in frying pan.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Cut up onion to cover.
Combine sauce ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 450° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix Dream Whip.
Follow directions on box.
Set aside.
Peel brown off of angel food cake slowly.
Dip out small slices of white cake and layer in bottom of bowl, then put a layer of Dream Whip, then a layer of cherries.
Repeat until ingredients are gone.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch. Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 10-inch skillet until beef is brown.
Drain and stir in seasoning mix.
Spoon into baking dish.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut off tops at stem ends and remove seeds and membrane. Reserve tops.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the ground meat, rice, onion, celery and egg. Blend well. Add half and half, tomato sauce, salt and peppers.
Mix to blend well.
Place green peppers in an ovenproof dish upright. Fill green peppers with mixture, mounding a little on top.
Filling will shrink while baking. Bake at 400° for about 35 minutes or until filling is set and cooked thoroughly and peppers are tender. Serve immediately. Makes 4 servings.

title: hash
directions: Cook roasts overnight, covered in water, in a large heavy-duty pot.
Let meat cool enough to be able to tear apart and throw away fat from bones.
Twist the meat into a fine texture; return the meat to broth in pot.
Continue cooking on low heat and add onions, margarine, salt and pepper.
Let simmer for 20 to 24 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: peanut patties
directions: Bring sugar, water and syrup to a boil.
Add peanuts and coloring.
Continue boiling over medium heat to "hard ball" stage (about 20 minutes).
Add butter and beat until thick enough to drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: millionaires' pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together condensed milk and lemon juice.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Freeze one and refrigerate the other several hours before serving.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook in a 9-inch pie crust for 1 hour at 275°.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Combine the flour, cayenne pepper and Rice Krispies with the cheese and margarine.
Roll in small balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake on ungreased pan for 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased loaf pan. Bake at 400° about 40 minutes.

title: apple walnut sticky buns
directions: Prepare Glaze:
Grease 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups (see note).
In small saucepan over low heat, stir honey and butter just until butter melts. Remove from heat. Stir in cinnamon. Place about 1 tablespoon glaze mixture in each greased muffin pan cup.
Set remaining glaze aside.
Add 1 teaspoon each brown sugar and chopped walnuts to each cup.
Set muffin pan aside.

title: best ever chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in mixing bowl. Bring to a boil the margarine, baking cocoa and water. Pour over flour mixture and mix well. Beat in eggs. Add buttermilk, soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla and mix well. Spoon into a greased and floured 12 x 17-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frosty strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Gradually add ice cream, stirring until melted.
Then chill until thickened but not set, 15 to 25 minutes.
Fold in strawberries and pour into crust.
Chill until firm 20 to 30 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream or topping. Other flavors of gelatin and other fruits may be used but do not use sherbets.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Press mixture into a loaf pan.
Bake one hour and 15 minutes.

title: southern comfort cake
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine berries, sugar and orange.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water, then add ice cubes and all ingredients.
Chill until firm. Serve on lettuce.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix Bisquick mix, milk and 2 tablespoons of mayonnaise. Spread in 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
(Dough will be sticky.) Mix sausage (browned), onion, grated cheese, egg and mayonnaise.
Mix and spread over dough.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Chop onion in small pieces.
Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake for 35 minutes or until bubbly in a 350° oven.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well, adding zucchini, dates and nuts last. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecue smoked sausage
directions: Slice smoked sausage in half; cut into 1 inch slices.
Pour barbecue sauce over sausage.
Slice green pepper and onion; lay over top.
Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. To use on grill wrap in aluminum foil and broil on grill.

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Chill until serving time.

title: eileen's bologna sandwich spread
directions: Grind bologna, eggs and pickles together (food processor is good for this).
Moisten to your taste with salad dressing.
MMMM good!

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chill before serving.

title: lamb in casserole
directions: Cut lamb in uniform pieces and roll in seasoned flour.
Brown in drippings.
Place in casserole.
Add carrots, onions, parsley and cover with cold water.
Cook in moderate oven until meat is tender.
Add more seasonings if necessary.
Thicken the gravy with flour.
Time in oven 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: easy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt cocoa and margarine in large sauce pan over the lowest heat possible, stirring constantly until thoroughly combined.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix thoroughly. Sift together flour, salt, and baking powder and add to sauce pan, mixing thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts, if desired.
Stir gently until vanilla is absorbed.
Pour into baking pan and bake for 20 minutes, no longer.
Longer baking makes a hard, dry brownie. Cool.
Frost with chocolate frosting (any variety) or dust with powdered sugar.
Will serve 12 to 16 people depending how large a brownie you want.

title: ham and cheese potato salad
directions: Melt butter; add onion and cook until tender (5 minutes). Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens.
In a 2-quart greased casserole, layer half the potatoes, ham cubes and sauce.
Repeat layers and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake covered at 375° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake for 15 to 20 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Mix crushed Oreos and 1/2 cup margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze for 30 minutes.
Spread 1/2 gallon softened vanilla ice cream evenly over cookie base.
Freeze.

title: baked noodles and bologna
directions: Combine the
chopped bologna, noodles, salt, pepper and milk. Mix well.
With
the
butter,
grease
a baking pan and pour the noodle mix in baking pan.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over noodles. Sprinkle with
butter
and
bake
to 35 minutes. Serves 5 to 7.

title: caramel and chocolate cookie bar
directions: In a heavy pan combine caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until caramels are melted.
Set aside.

title: chicken 'n rice("arroz con pollo")
directions: Boil chicken in water for 1 hour.
Debone chicken.
Mix all remaining ingredients in Dutch oven, along with the deboned chicken.
Cook over slow heat for 1 hour.

title: orange slice bread
directions: Cut dates and orange slices with kitchen scissors into small pieces.
Dredge in 1 cup flour.
Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and soda dissolved in buttermilk.
Add 3 cups flour, date and orange slices.
Mix well and bake in 2 loaf pans, greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: date bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg, 1 at a time; beat well.
Blend in flour, baking powder; add nuts and dates.
