Spread in a 10 x 15-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cut in pieces and roll in powdered sugar.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put long
green cucumbers in quart jars.
Bring to boil water, vinegar and salt.
Pour over jars of cucumbers.

title: black-eyed peas with bacon
directions: Place peas, bacon and enough water to cover in a large kettle; bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from the heat; cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Do not drain.
In a skillet, saute onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Add to pea mixture with thyme and salt.
Return to the heat; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until peas are soft.
Top with crumbled bacon, if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mimosa
directions: Mix equal parts of champagne and orange juice.
Great with brunch.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute onions in oil until slightly browned.
Add garlic and saute 1 to 2 additional minutes.
Stir in crushed tomatoes, celery, chili powder, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and pepper sauce.
Bring to a boil.

title: broken toffee
directions: Cook sugar, salt, water and butter to 285° or until a few drops of mixture added to a cup of water will form a thin pliable ribbon.
Add 1/2 cup of nuts.
Pour onto a well-greased cookie sheet; cool.
Melt chocolate; spread on top.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts; cool.
This will make about 2 dozen pieces.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Fry fish in 375° hot fat until done, about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cube cooked
potatoes.	Mix
with bacon and onion.
Mix mayonnaise,
sugar	and vinegar together with seasoning.
Pour over other ingredients; serve warm.

title: choco-nut pie
directions: Mix
all
together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: oven "fried" parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine egg and milk; combine cheese, flour, paprika, salt and pepper in another bowl.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture; coat with flour mixture.
Place pieces in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter over chicken and bake 1 hour.

title: watermelon preserves
directions: Peel all green off rind.
It is best if 1/4 to 1/2-inch of red fruit is still on rind.
Cut into small cubes.
Wash twice.

title: crispy buttermilk chicken(ultra low-fat)
directions: Mix together buttermilk, garlic salt, garlic and black pepper. Dip chicken breasts in mixture and roll in cornflakes.
Bake on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Makes 4 servings.
Calories per serving, 260; fat per serving, 4.5.

title: crispy pepper skin duckling(or chicken)
directions: Rub
duck
inside
and	outside
with
mixture of green onion, ginger, sake, salt, Szechwan peppercorn salt and anise. Let stand 30	minutes.
Place duck in steamer and steam for 2 to 2
1/2 hours
over medium heat.
Remove and rub surface of duck with shoyu.
Deep
fry
in
hot	oil (could be split for easier handling
and faster time), over high heat until golden brown and crisp, about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cut into bite size pieces. Arrange
on
platter; garnish with coriander.
May be served with 5 spice salt for dipping.
Heat a pan (no oil) and stir-fry salt over
low
heat until very hot.
Remove and mix with 5 spice powder or Szechwan peppercorn powder.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water until almost tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until glazed.
Serves 4.

title: beef stew
directions: Cook beef to just about done, then cut up into pieces.
Add all the ingredients and cook until done.

title: pineapple coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into three cake pans.
Bake at 325° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until center springs up when touched.

title: tabooley(lebanese wheat salad)
directions: Soak the cracked wheat in water for 15 minutes; drain dry. Dice onions and tomatoes.
Cut the parsley into small pieces with kitchen shears.
Mix all well.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with sprigs of fresh mint and black olives.
Serves 6.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Place pie filling in a small casserole dish.
Top with flour. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Boil together slowly white sugar, brown sugar, butter and Carnation milk until forms a soft ball when dropped in water. Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Mix together chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Keep stirring until smooth.
Pour in a 9 x 13 baking pan and let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream peanut butter, Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs; blend.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add vanilla; mix again.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet.
Spank the cookies.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: hamburger-beef
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire and simmer 5 minutes with a little water.
Add beans, ketchup and garlic; simmer 1/2 hour or until ready to serve.
Great over boiled potatoes!

title: chocolate mint tea
directions: Blend mint tea and hot chocolate in a saucepan and heat.
Add creme de menthe.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream and mint. (Serves 8.)

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa powder, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, melted margarine and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour batter into 8 or 9-inch square pan.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients and form into a ball. Color with red food coloring, if desired, to make pretty for parties.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: goodie bar
directions: Mix all three ingredients together thoroughly.
Pat out in a 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle pecan and chocolate chips over it.
Beat powdered sugar, cream cheese and eggs together.
Pour over other ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and just enough milk to make a paste. Next, stir in remaining milk. In a saucepan on medium heat, cook the mixture slowly until the gravy thickens. Add some butter or let each one add their own. Serve over hot biscuits. Makes about 4 servings.

title: corn salsa
directions: Combine and refrigerate. Serve with a simple green salad for a colorful, nutritious lunch!

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour in pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: scrambled egg and bacon casserole
directions: Mix butter, salt, flour and pepper well and cook over low heat.
Add milk; stir well.
Continue cooking over low heat.
Add Velveeta or Cheez Whiz to the white sauce mixture; continue cooking over low heat, stirring until it thickens a bit.
Combine with eggs and bacon.
Stir gently, but well.
Toast bread; dice and crumble.
Toss with butter.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs over egg mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
(May be refrigerated overnight before baking.
This is a good breakfast for overnight guests. Serve with muffins or such.)

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk, sugar and salt and cook for about 3/4 hour. Rice will be soft, but milk will not be completely absorbed.
Set aside.
Beat eggs with vanilla until frothy.
Mix well and quickly. Put into rice and continue stirring to keep eggs and rice at this consistency.
Spread in serving pan and sprinkle cinnamon while hot.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Note: Mushrooms and pimentos are optional.

title: pizza quick
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 2 more cups Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake in 425° oven until cheese is melted and golden brown.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
In a casserole dish, layer Doritos. Add deboned chicken.
Add Ro-Tel.
Add cream of mushroom soup, then cream of chicken soup.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in greased 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour.
Cook lasagna noodles.
In 13 x 9-inch pan, spread 1/2 cup tomato sauce, layer noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese, until pan is filled.
Top with sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: Blend together and refrigerate.

title: broiled pork chops
directions: Combine oil, wine, garlic powder and dash of pepper; set aside.
Trim chops of excess fat.
Place chops on rack of an unheated broiler pan.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 10 to 12 minutes; brush with some of wine mixture.

title: herb dip
directions: Thoroughly mix together and mold into shape.
Refrigerate overnight.
If using fresh herbs, use twice as much as called for.

title: fresh dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with raw vegetables or Fritos.

title: cranapple salad
directions: Wash and drain cranberries before grinding.
Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate. Yield: 2 quarts.

title: pickled walnuts
directions: To each quart of vinegar allow 2 ounces of pepper, 1 ounce of allspice and 1 ounce of ginger.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Prepare salad dressing according to package directions; set aside.
Chop cauliflower, broccoli, olives, onion, water chestnuts and tomatoes.
Mix well and pour dressing over vegetables.
Mix well and marinate for 24 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cook sausage, crumble into dry mixture of cheese and bisquick.
Add water and combine until well blended.
Form into small balls (about 40).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: pretzel animals
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix yeast, water, sugar and salt.
Add flour a little at a time.
Knead until smooth.
Shape small amounts of dough into animal shapes.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle lightly with salt. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese into a soft dough. Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake for about 15 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli and onion.
In separate bowl, mix mayo, sugar and vinegar; pour over broccoli and onion.
Add cheese; chill 2 hours before serving.
Add bacon.

title: baked ginger pears
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pears, reserving juice.
Arrange pear halves close together in a baking dish, cut side up.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine brown sugar, lemon juice, ginger and pecans; mix well.
Spoon into pear halves and sprinkle lightly with ginger.
Pour reserved pear juice around pears to cover bottom of dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook linguini, mix in green peppers and tomatoes.
Pour in Italian dressing and McCormick Salad Supreme seasoning.
Mix well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: head cheese
directions: Cook snoots and ears together, adding salt, black pepper, red pepper and sage.
After meat is cooked, separate from bones.
Put in food processor or mix by hand until meat is fine, adding more seasoning according to taste.
Add vinegar according to taste.
Mix all together and heat through.
Put in container and refrigerate. Next day, cut in serving pieces.

title: chicken with spanish rice
directions: Boil
the
chicken
with the rosemary until tender; pull off the bone and cut into small pieces.
Meanwhile, saute onion with garlic
in
olive
oil.
Add
the tomato and lightly saute with the
onion
garlic mixture.
Add chicken and cook covered for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add mixture to the hot, cooked rice and mix.
Steam for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 1/4 cup of cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in 1/2 cup milk, butter and vanilla.
Spread into a buttered 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa over the batter.
Pour remaining 1 1/2 cups milk over all.
Bake until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on a rack to room temperature before serving. "Excellent with ice cream."

title: winona's cheese cake
directions: Chill evaporated milk.
Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water and cool.
Cream 1 cup sugar with cream cheese.
When jello is cooled, mix with cream cheese.
Whip chilled milk to thicken it.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into a large graham cracker crust.
Add drained pineapple, if desired.

title: tom and jerrie batter
directions: Beat egg whites first until stiff as possible, but not dry. Add 1/2 cup granulated sugar and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Beat until like whipped cream.
Follow the same with the yolks.
Mix together with a spoon.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bring mixture of fruit juice, cornstarch, sugar and lemon juice to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Bake sugar cookies on one sheet so that 1 large cookie is made using directions on package. Cream Cool Whip and cream cheese together until smooth.
Spread on cooled cookie.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese and Cool Whip mixture.
Make sauce and cool.
Pour over fruit.
Serve chilled.

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese at
room temperature.
Cut ham into cubes and chop green onions.	In bowl, mix all ingredients together, mix well and
form
into
ball.
Keep
cool
in
refrigerator. Serve on a platter with different kinds of crackers all around the cheese ball.
Excellent for parties, especially at Christmas.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Place corned beef in a pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil, then turn down heat and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
The last hour of cooking, add cut up vegetables.
Cook until tender.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot.
Add one tomato juice can full of water.
Liquid should cover vegetables and bones.
If it doesn't, add little more water.
Put soup pot over high heat and bring to a boil, then immediately turn down heat.
Take a spoon and carefully scoop foam off top of soup and throw away.
Cook soup, uncovered, at a simmer.
Don't let it boil.
Simmer for about 3 1/2 hours so flavors have a chance to mingle.
Stir once or twice during cooking.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: heavenly biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pan.
Knead dough.
Cut into shapes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Layer 1 (bottom of pan):
2 cans bean dip.

title: the night before breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage; drain.
Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour eggs on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pink fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix and slow cook 4 to 5 hours.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter, sugar and shortening.
Sift together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix together.
Form balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 4 tablespoons sugar and 4 tablespoons cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna mango spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in small bowl. Mix very well. Serve on crackers or Melba toast. It's great for parties.

title: greek lemon rice soup
directions: Bring broth and water to boil.
Add rice; boil 14 minutes. Beat eggs well.
Add 1/2 cup broth to lemon juice; add this mix to eggs very slowly, beating constantly.
Add lemon-egg mix to chicken rice broth.

title: spinach quiche(short-cut version)
directions: Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Combine spinach, onion, garlic, cheese, milk and seasonings.
Turn into pastry lined pie plate.
Arrange thinly sliced tomatoes on top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven setting to 350°.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan and bread crumbs over top.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: beet nut salad
directions: Drain liquid from beets and pineapple into cooking pot. Add water, juice and vinegar. Add sugar and heat. Dissolve Jell-O into this mixture. Add beets and pineapple. Spread chopped nuts on top. Chill.

title: microwave german chocolate cake
directions: Beat together all ingredients except frosting for 3 minutes. put in lightly greased microwavable cake pan.
Spoon frosting on top and bake for 9 minutes at power level 5, then 11 minutes at high power level 10.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in baking dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: basic no-fat chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 13 x 9-inch cake pan with Pam.
Heat milk in medium size saucepan until barely simmering.
Remove from heat and whisk in cocoa until thickened and almost smooth.
Let stand 2 or 3 minutes to cool.
Whisk in applesauce and vanilla. Mix flour, 1 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Beat egg whites in medium size bowl with mixer on high until thick and foamy.
Gradually beat in remaining 1/4 cup sugar until stiff peaks form.
Pour cocoa mixture over flour. Stir just until blended.
With rubber spatula, gently stir abut 1/4 egg whites into flour mixture.
Fold in remaining egg whites until no white streaks remain.
Pour into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Makes 30 servings.
133 calories per serving, .3 grams fat.

title: soy sauce marinade
directions: Mix with a basting brush to dissolve brown sugar.
Poke holes in
meat with large fork and pour mixture over it.
Turn often during the day to make sure meat is fully marinated.

title: banana sticky buns
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 2 teaspoons brown sugar, 2 teaspoons butter and 3 pecan halves in each of 12 muffin cups.
Place in oven to melt sugar and butter.
Stir baking mix and banana to a soft dough.
Gently smooth into ball; knead 5 times.
Roll into 15 x 9 inch rectangle.
Spread with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar.
Roll up.
Begin at long side.
Pinch edge of dough into roll to seal.
Cut roll into 12 (1 1/4-inch) slices. Place slices cut side down in muffin cups.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt butter and saute onion and celery.
Combine all ingredients with cooked rice and saute mixture.
Spread into casserole dish and bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.

title: potato croquettes
directions: Peel and wash potatoes.
Cut into quarters.
Cook in boiling water until soft.
Drain.
Stand the pan of potatoes over the lowest possible heat and mash finely.
Add butter, cheese, egg yolks, nutmeg, salt and pepper to taste.
When mixture is cool enough to handle, form into cork shapes.
Coat lightly with beaten egg white and crumbs.
Heat oil until a cube of bread dropped into it turns golden in 1 minute and floats to top.
Fry croquettes until golden.
Drain on paper towel.

title: spaghetti a la terrant
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Pour off excessive fat and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: cherry candy
directions: Mix all ingredients well and roll into small balls.
Chill at least 30 minutes.
When well chilled, lift each ball with a toothpick and dip into chocolate mixture made by melting chocolate chips with paraffin.
Chill until set.

title: lemon pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box; cool. Cream the margarine and cream cheese together. Add powdered sugar until thoroughly mixed. Add vanilla and mix. Spread over cake. Spoon pineapple over topping.

title: della robbia ice ring(for fruit medley punch)
directions: Combine cans of ginger ale and 1/2 cup ReaLemon brand.
Pour 2 1/2 cups mixture into 1 quart ring mold.
Arrange apricot halves, green grapes, strawberries, orange peel strips or any other fruits and mint leaves on top of ice.
Slowly pour remaining ReaLemon brand mixture over fruit.
Freeze.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook rice and broccoli.
Add soup, onion, celery and cheese; mix.
Salt, pepper and butter to taste. Bake about 30 minutes at 325°.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cocoa peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in a saucepan; add margarine and milk. Bring to a boiling point, stirring constantly, and boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and pecans. Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool thoroughly before serving or storing.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients (by hand or mixer).
Do not use nonstick spray or butter on griddle.
Makes approx. ten 4-inch pancakes.

title: short-cut chili sauce
directions: Hand cutting vegetables is important.
Boil together for 10 minutes the tomatoes, celery, onions and peppers.
Add salt and let stand overnight.
Drain in colander, do not press.
Return to pan.
Add sugar, brown sugar, vinegar and pepper.
Put pickling spices, cinnamon and ginger in spice bag.
Add to mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes and can.
Very good.
Do not double recipe.

title: layered salad
directions: Place lettuce in shallow dish.
Top with onion, celery and water chestnuts.
Cover with a layer of frozen peas, followed by a layer of mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with sugar, Parmesan, salt and garlic.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
At serving time top with boiled eggs and bacon.

title: theresa's chili
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In a large kettle, mix beans, juice, paprika, red pepper and chili powder.
Tie cloves and bay leaf in a piece of cheesecloth and add to juice bean mixture.
Add browned ingredients to juice bean mixture.
Mix all ingredients well.
Let all ingredients simmer over medium heat for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: In a shallow 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole, beat eggs with wooden spoon until foamy.
Add corn, melted butter and onion dip. Beat until blended.
Stir in muffin mix.
Bake in a 325° oven 28 to 30 minutes or until knife stuck in center comes out clean.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature and mix with mayonnaise and Hidden Valley Ranch Dressing mix.
Set aside.
Roll crescent dough on cookie sheet to form a rectangle.
Press edges together and brush with beaten egg.
Bake according to package directions, then cool.
When dough has cooled, press down bubbles with bottom of spoon.
Spread dough with cream cheese mixture. Then sprinkle with vegetables followed by cheese.
Cover with saran wrap and press vegetables into crust.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Combine soups, sour cream and chili for sauce and heat until smooth.
Mix cheese and green onions together.
Dip tortillas in hot oil for a second to soften.
Place cheese mixture and chicken across center of tortilla.
Add 1 tablespoon sauce.
Roll.
Place side by side, seam down, in baking dish.
Pour sauce and sprinkle more cheese mixture over the top.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly. Garnish with chopped green onions.
Can be frozen and reheated.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter.
Remove from pan. Brown hamburger.
Stir in corn, olives and tomatoes.
Stir and cook 3 minutes.
Mix in seasonings, onion and bell pepper.
In casserole dish, stack layers of meat mixture, tortillas and cheese.
Top with olives and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot cider
directions: Put brown sugar, cloves and cinnamon sticks in basket of coffeepot.
Put apple and cranberry juices into coffeepot and let perk until cycle is complete.
Use only half of ingredients for a 9 cup coffeepot.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in boiling salted water until tender.
Cool. Remove chicken and debone.
In broth, cook onion and green pepper. After 5 minutes, add spaghetti.
When done, add chicken.
May need to remove some of the broth.
Add cheese; let melt.
May serve now or put in casserole.
Freezes well.

title: salmon loaf supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9 x 5 loaf pan.
In large bowl, with fork, beat eggs slightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into pan.
Shape into loaf and bake for 45 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour onto hot griddle.
Makes 10 large pancakes.

title: caesar salad dressing
directions: Blend eggs in blender; add anchovy paste.
Add rest of ingredients except mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Blend well. Empty mayonnaise in large mixing bowl.
Pour contents of blender over mayonnaise and mix by hand.
Add lemon juice and parsley. Chill.
Keep in refrigerator 4 to 6 weeks.
Serve with croutons.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix at least 12 hours before you intend to use.
Excellent on all kinds of crackers.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust and set aside.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Boil for 3 minutes until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add jello until dissolved.
Cool mixture.
Place sliced strawberries in cooled pie crust.
Pour jello mixture over strawberries.
Cool for 1 hour.
Top with whipped topping and serve.

title: raspberry hearts
directions: Beat egg.
Stir in sugar, almond and vanilla.
Cream butter and combine with egg mixture.
Mix in flour.
Form into 2 balls and flatten into discs.
Chill until firm.
Remove 1 disc at a time and roll to 1/8-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into heart shapes with 3 or 4-inch cookie cutter.
Take remaining hearts and using smaller cookie cutter, cut out center to create border of heart.
Spoon 1/2 teaspoon preserves in center of hearts and top with heart border.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle cookie edges with powdered sugar.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.
Delicious!

title: chicken chasseurs
directions: Coat chicken with seasoned flour, to which thyme had been added.
In hot butter in a large skillet, saute chicken until golden on all sides.
Add scallions, mushrooms, sugar, salt, lemon juice, apple juice and tomatoes.
Cook slowly, covered, for 35 to 45 minutes, or until chicken is fork tender.
Sprinkle with parsley and chives.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: perfect noodles every time
directions: Mix together, knead on floured surface about four or five times, then roll and cut.
Let dry for about 30 minutes, then chop into your broth and cook about 30 minutes.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Pack jars with cucumbers.
Mix all other ingredients and heat until sugar is melted.
Pour over cucumbers and store in jars in refrigerator.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13 x 2-inch sheet cake pan.
Layer pecans and coconut in pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions.
Pour cake mix over top of coconut.

title: arctic mousse
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press onto bottom of an 8-inch square pan.
Combine Marshmallow Creme, chocolate and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Gradually add milk; blend until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pan; freeze.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs with a hand Swiss beater.
Add milk and remaining ingredients.
Put mixture into uncooked pie shells. (Cover pie crust with cornstarch.)
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: mexican mocha balls
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients. Stir together flour, cocoa, coffee and salt. Gradually beat dry mix into creamed mix. Stir in nuts and cherries. Chill 1 hour. Bake on ungreased sheet at 325° for 20 minutes. While warm, dust with fine sugar. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: hand lotion
directions: Soak gum overnight in cistern water.
Strain and simmer on back of stove several hours.
Lastly add perfume oil and bottle.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Chop meat.
Cook noodles in 1 quart of water; drain.
Mix fat, flour and milk together.
Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 15.
Can be frozen.

title: carrot custard
directions: Cook and mash carrots.
Beat eggs and mix together with milk, salt, butter and sugar.
Grate cheese and add to the other ingredients, including the bread crumbs.
Place mixture in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake for about 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Serves 8 to 10.

title: dump it cake
directions: Grease an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Dump applesauce into it.
Dump crushed pineapple on top of that.
Spread dry cake mix over that. Melt butter and pour over dry cake mix.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups chopped nuts over butter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Top with whipped cream.

title: heloise's roach exterminating formula
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; mix boric acid, flour and onion. Add to sugar and shortening.
Blend well, then add water to form soft dough balls.
(If balls are placed in opened plastic sandwich bags, the dough will stay softer longer.)
Place balls throughout the house in places normally inhabited by roaches.
When dough becomes brick hard, replace with a fresh batch.
Keep out of reach of children and pets.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind all together and blend in sugar.	Let stand overnight.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and margarine.
Add crushed graham crackers, cherries and pecans (use the juice from the cherries also).
Mix well and spread in a Bundt pan.
Cool and keep refrigerated.

title: baked salmon
directions: Cover the fillets with the above ingredients as listed.
Bake on aluminum foil or shallow pan in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rosy apple whirls
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to boil for 5 minutes, then pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1/2 for later.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in 1/3 cup Crisco until particles are formed.
Break 1 egg into measuring cup.
Add milk to measure 2/3 cups.
Beat with fork to combine.

title: quick rolls
directions: Stir really well, then pour in greased muffin tin. Bake at 450°. Makes 12 rolls.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding per instructions on box.
Whip sour cream and whipped cream into pudding.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding; repeat.
For an Epworth gathering I double the recipe.
Serves 6.

title: aunt mamie's muffins
directions: Mix everything except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold in.
Bake at 350°.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Partially prepare the night before.
Combine buttermilk and oats.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, mix together flours, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat 2 eggs.
Add butter; blend.
Add oatmeal mixture.
Blend in flour.
Batter will be very thick so you might want to add a few tablespoons of buttermilk but no more than 4 tablespoons.
Fry pancakes on electric griddle at 345°.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add milk, vanilla, salt and coconut.
Pour melted butter over mixture after it has been poured into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Put small amounts of oatmeal in blender until all oatmeal is powder. Mix flour, oatmeal, salt, soda and baking powder together; stir into butter and egg mixture.

title: cookie candy
directions: Mix together in a 1-quart saucepan the sugar, milk, cocoa and butter or margarine.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Let boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Mix well.
Cool on a buttered plate or pan.

title: salmon roll
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans and parsley.
Mix well. Chill for 3 to 5 hours.
Shape into log and roll in nuts and parsley.
Chill and serve with crackers.
Keep refrigerated.

title: lemon angel dessert
directions: Combine lemon juice, sugar and sweetened condensed milk.
Add whipped topping.
Tear cake into small pieces and line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture over cake and mix slightly. Chill for 24 hours before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: joanna's monkey bread
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease angel food cake or Bundt cake pan and spread with chopped pecans. Quarter biscuits and coat with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in baking pan and pour remaining sugar mixture over biscuits.
In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter, syrup and water. Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse(makes 8 servings)
directions: Add chips into blender.
Pour boiling water into blender.
Add yolks, one at a time.
Add the sugar.
Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Fold mixture and Cool Whip into a bowl.
Pour into dessert dishes and refrigerate.

title: "sos" or creamed hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add flour and stir.
(If meat is very lean, add a little oil or shortening.)
Add milk until thick like gravy or cream sauce.
Add salt and pepper.
Serve over toast.

title: anisette cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend first 4 ingredients.
Mix next 3 dry ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with colored sugar while still hot.

title: baked squash
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Mash and add butter, egg, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 bread crumbs.
Place in greased baking dish and top with remaining cheese and remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese browns lightly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well and let set overnight.
Serve on a bed of lettuce or without, if you prefer.
The Tang seems to prevent the bananas from discoloring.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes with a fork.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until tender.
Cool slightly.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Gently scoop out each potato half, leaving a thin shell.
Set shells aside.
Put pulp into a small mixing bowl.
Add cream cheese, chives, basil, salt and pepper; beat until smooth. Add milk, a teaspoon at a time, beating until potato mixture is fluffy.
Pipe or spoon potato mixture into shells.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place on a baking sheet.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more or until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions together until soft.
Drain well and mash.
Add carrots, soup and sour cream.
Soften stuffing with butter and add to squash mixture.
Spread in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix celery, cheese, pimento, onion and mayonnaise.
Add peas last and mix lightly.
Chill overnight.

title: zesty shrimp dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy and light.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with fresh vegetables. Yield: 1 2/3 cups.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Shape into balls and place on sheet.
Chill in freezer until nice and sassy.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In heavy skillet, brown ground beef, garlic and onion; add salt and pepper.
Stir flour into ground beef until brown.
Mix cream of chicken soup with water and pour into ground beef.
Stir until mixture comes to boil.
Turn heat to low and simmer 30 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: lychee chicken salad
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken, water, onion, ginger, salt and 1/2 teaspoon curry. Cover and bring to boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cool chicken in stock and cut into chunks.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in three 9-inch cake pans.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake on large cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Stir occasionally.
Cool and stir with fork until crumbly.
Store in covered jar.
Serve with dried apricots, raisins, dates and yogurt.

title: chicken spaghetti for 12
directions: Boil hen until tender and bone.
Melt margarine and saute peppers, celery, onions, garlic and mushrooms until tender.
Add tomato soup, chicken, pimento and bay leaf. Cook slowly for 2 hours. Cook spaghetti separately and add when ready to serve. Add cheese last and let melt into all before serving.
Serves 12.

title: chili
directions: Saute onion and hamburger.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Cook until tomatoes cook apart.
Serve with crackers.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, corn
syrup and water, stirring until sugar dissolves.	Then cook
over
heat,	without
stirring, to hard ball stage (265°).	Test by
dropping
a few drops in a cup of cold water.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix
graham
cracker
crumbs,
sugar and oleo (melted). Spread in 9
x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.	Mix Eagle Brand
milk
and coconut.
Spread over crust and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter. Spread over top.
Cool and cut in bars.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Spread into bottom of pie shell.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool.
Brush with syrup and garnish with nuts.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage and drain off grease.
Mix sausage with remaining ingredients.
Shape into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve the yeast in the warm water with the tablespoon of sugar added first.
Let set to foam.
Add buttermilk and yeast mixture to dry ingredients; mix well.
Put on floured board.
Add more flour, if needed, to handle good.
Roll out, cut and then dip in melted margarine.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done. (Different ovens vary in temperature.)

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip all ingredients together and chill.

title: cajun dirty rice
directions: Remove hard membranes from giblets; chop or grind in food processor.
Put skillet over high heat.
When hot, add 2 tablespoons oil; add giblets and beef.
Cook, stirring, until no longer pink (approximately 4 minutes).
Using a slotted spoon, transfer to bowl and set aside.
Pour remaining oil in skillet. When oil is hot, add celery, red pepper and chopped onion.
Stir until vegetables are soft (approximately 7 minutes).
Sprinkle in flour, oregano and cayenne pepper.
Cook until flour is browned (approximately 2 to 3 minutes).
Pour in broth; bring to boil; stir in giblets and beef.
Add rice; stir until heated.
Add green onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and butter.
Roll into balls.
Place on waxed paper.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: easy chicken gravy
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in small sauce pan.
Add flour - a couple of tablespoons at a time and stir until a ball is formed from the flour and butter in the pan. Pour about 1/4 cup of chicken broth and stir until smooth.
Keep adding a little of the chicken broth and stirring until smooth each time. If gravy is too thick, add a little water and stir until smooth until desired thickness. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes about 1 1/2
to 2 cups gravy.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch; cook until clear and remove from heat.
Add jello; let cool.
Put fresh strawberries into pie shell and pour sauce over strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Saute the onion and the celery in the butter in a large skillet until tender.
Add the parsley, crab meat, cheese, evaporated milk, soup, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook for 15 minutes or until the cheese is melted and the mixture is heated through, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with crackers.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients except nuts.
Chill for several hours. Form into ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Saute the bell pepper, onion and garlic.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Add Tabasco sauce, Worcestershire sauce, tomato paste, corn, olives and juice and pepper and onion with garlic. Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Drain.
Layer in casserole dish (13 x 9-inch) the noodles, sauce, cheese, etc.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place cooked broccoli in shallow baking dish.
Top with sliced chicken.
Sprinkle
cheese next.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon
juice
and
curry;
pour
this mixture over the chicken. Sprinkle
bread crumbs on top, along with additional cheese, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: egg and cheese
directions: Prepare a sauce of 1 1/2 tablespoons butter, flour, milk and seasoning. Melt remaining butter in casserole in oven. Add about 1/4 cup crumbs and set aside for top. Arrange in casserole in layers the remaining crumbs, eggs, cheese and sauce. Top with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° until sauce begins to bubble and top is brown. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken rice italia
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove excess fat from chicken; season with salt and oregano.
Remove and put aside 1/4 cup tomato sauce. Combine remaining sauce, rice, zucchini, water and salt in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; stir well.
Arrange chicken over rice mixture.
Cover tightly with foil; bake for 1 hour, or until chicken is tender and most of liquid is absorbed.
Spoon reserved sauce over chicken; sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 2 or 3 minutes to melt cheese.
Makes 6 servings (449 calories each).

title: sunshine lemon cookies
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk, lemon rind and lemon juice; beat well.
Gradually add flour; mix just until blended.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: lemon barbecued chicken
directions: The day before cooking, combine first 7 ingredients.
Pour over chicken pieces in a glass dish.
Refrigerate, covered.
Turn over several times in marinade.
